4174  * Return TRUE if "state" leads to a NFA_MATCH without advancing the input.
4175  */
4176  static int
4177 match_follows(nfa_state_T *startstate, int depth)
4178 {
4179  nfa_state_T *state = startstate;
4180 
4181  /* avoid too much recursion */
4182  if (depth > 10)
4183  return FALSE;
4184 
4185  while (state != NULL)
4186  {
4187  switch (state->c)
4188  {
4189  case NFA_MATCH:
4190  case NFA_MCLOSE:
4191  case NFA_END_INVISIBLE:
4192  case NFA_END_INVISIBLE_NEG:
4193  case NFA_END_PATTERN:
4194  return TRUE;
4195 
4196  case NFA_SPLIT:
4197  return match_follows(state->out, depth + 1)
4198  || match_follows(state->out1, depth + 1);
4199 
4200  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE:
4201  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_FIRST:
4202  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE:
4203  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_FIRST:
4204  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG:
4205  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG_FIRST:
4206  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG:
4207  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST:
4208  case NFA_COMPOSING:
4209  /* skip ahead to next state */
4210  state = state->out1->out;
4211  continue;
4212 
4213  case NFA_ANY:
4214  case NFA_ANY_COMPOSING:
4215  case NFA_IDENT:
4216  case NFA_SIDENT:
4217  case NFA_KWORD:
4218  case NFA_SKWORD:
4219  case NFA_FNAME:
4220  case NFA_SFNAME:
4221  case NFA_PRINT:
4222  case NFA_SPRINT:
4223  case NFA_WHITE:
4224  case NFA_NWHITE:
4225  case NFA_DIGIT:
4226  case NFA_NDIGIT:
4227  case NFA_HEX:
4228  case NFA_NHEX:
4229  case NFA_OCTAL:
4230  case NFA_NOCTAL:
4231  case NFA_WORD:
4232  case NFA_NWORD:
4233  case NFA_HEAD:
4234  case NFA_NHEAD:
4235  case NFA_ALPHA:
4236  case NFA_NALPHA:
4237  case NFA_LOWER:
4238  case NFA_NLOWER:
4239  case NFA_UPPER:
4240  case NFA_NUPPER:
4241  case NFA_LOWER_IC:
4242  case NFA_NLOWER_IC:
4243  case NFA_UPPER_IC:
4244  case NFA_NUPPER_IC:
4245  case NFA_START_COLL:
4246  case NFA_START_NEG_COLL:
4247  case NFA_NEWL:
4248  /* state will advance input */
4249  return FALSE;
4250 
4251  default:
4252  if (state->c > 0)
4253  /* state will advance input */
4254  return FALSE;
4255 
4256  /* Others: zero-width or possibly zero-width, might still find
4257  * a match at the same position, keep looking. */
4258  break;
4259  }
4260  state = state->out;
4261  }
4262  return FALSE;
4263 }
4264 
4265 
4266 /*
4267  * Return TRUE if "state" is already in list "l".
4268  */
4269  static int
4270 state_in_list(
4271  nfa_list_T *l, /* runtime state list */
4272  nfa_state_T *state, /* state to update */
4273  regsubs_T *subs) /* pointers to subexpressions */
4274 {
4275  if (state->lastlist[nfa_ll_index] == l->id)
4276  {
4277  if (!rex.nfa_has_backref || has_state_with_pos(l, state, subs, NULL))
4278  return TRUE;
4279  }
4280  return FALSE;
4281 }
4282 
4283 /* Offset used for "off" by addstate_here(). */
4284 #define ADDSTATE_HERE_OFFSET 10
4285 
4286 /*
4287  * Add "state" and possibly what follows to state list ".".
4288  * Returns "subs_arg", possibly copied into temp_subs.
4289  * Returns NULL when recursiveness is too deep.
4290  */
4291  static regsubs_T *
4292 addstate(
4293  nfa_list_T *l, /* runtime state list */
4294  nfa_state_T *state, /* state to update */
4295  regsubs_T *subs_arg, /* pointers to subexpressions */
4296  nfa_pim_T *pim, /* postponed look-behind match */
4297  int off_arg) /* byte offset, when -1 go to next line */
4298 {
4299  int subidx;
4300  int off = off_arg;
4301  int add_here = FALSE;
4302  int listindex = 0;
4303  int k;
4304  int found = FALSE;
4305  nfa_thread_T *thread;
4306  struct multipos save_multipos;
4307  int save_in_use;
4308  char_u *save_ptr;
4309  int i;
4310  regsub_T *sub;
4311  regsubs_T *subs = subs_arg;
4312  static regsubs_T temp_subs;
4313 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
4314  int did_print = FALSE;
4315 #endif
4316  static int depth = 0;
4317 
4318  // This function is called recursively. When the depth is too much we run
4319  // out of stack and crash, limit recursiveness here.
4320  if (++depth >= 5000 || subs == NULL)
4321  {
4322  --depth;
4323  return NULL;
4324  }
4325 
4326  if (off_arg <= -ADDSTATE_HERE_OFFSET)
4327  {
4328  add_here = TRUE;
4329  off = 0;
4330  listindex = -(off_arg + ADDSTATE_HERE_OFFSET);
4331  }
4332 
4333  switch (state->c)
4334  {
4335  case NFA_NCLOSE:
4336  case NFA_MCLOSE:
4337  case NFA_MCLOSE1:
4338  case NFA_MCLOSE2:
4339  case NFA_MCLOSE3:
4340  case NFA_MCLOSE4:
4341  case NFA_MCLOSE5:
4342  case NFA_MCLOSE6:
4343  case NFA_MCLOSE7:
4344  case NFA_MCLOSE8:
4345  case NFA_MCLOSE9:
4346 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
4347  case NFA_ZCLOSE:
4348  case NFA_ZCLOSE1:
4349  case NFA_ZCLOSE2:
4350  case NFA_ZCLOSE3:
4351  case NFA_ZCLOSE4:
4352  case NFA_ZCLOSE5:
4353  case NFA_ZCLOSE6:
4354  case NFA_ZCLOSE7:
4355  case NFA_ZCLOSE8:
4356  case NFA_ZCLOSE9:
4357 #endif
4358  case NFA_MOPEN:
4359  case NFA_ZEND:
4360  case NFA_SPLIT:
4361  case NFA_EMPTY:
4362  /* These nodes are not added themselves but their "out" and/or
4363  * "out1" may be added below. */
4364  break;
4365 
4366  case NFA_BOL:
4367  case NFA_BOF:
4368  /* "^" won't match past end-of-line, don't bother trying.
4369  * Except when at the end of the line, or when we are going to the
4370  * next line for a look-behind match. */
4371  if (rex.input > rex.line
4372  && *rex.input != NUL
4373  && (nfa_endp == NULL
4374  || !REG_MULTI
4375  || rex.lnum == nfa_endp->se_u.pos.lnum))
4376  goto skip_add;
4377  /* FALLTHROUGH */
4378 
4379  case NFA_MOPEN1:
4380  case NFA_MOPEN2:
4381  case NFA_MOPEN3:
4382  case NFA_MOPEN4:
4383  case NFA_MOPEN5:
4384  case NFA_MOPEN6:
4385  case NFA_MOPEN7:
4386  case NFA_MOPEN8:
4387  case NFA_MOPEN9:
4388 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
4389  case NFA_ZOPEN:
4390  case NFA_ZOPEN1:
4391  case NFA_ZOPEN2:
4392  case NFA_ZOPEN3:
4393  case NFA_ZOPEN4:
4394  case NFA_ZOPEN5:
4395  case NFA_ZOPEN6:
4396  case NFA_ZOPEN7:
4397  case NFA_ZOPEN8:
4398  case NFA_ZOPEN9:
4399 #endif
4400  case NFA_NOPEN:
4401  case NFA_ZSTART:
4402  /* These nodes need to be added so that we can bail out when it
4403  * was added to this list before at the same position to avoid an
4404  * endless loop for "\(\)*" */
4405 
4406  default:
4407  if (state->lastlist[nfa_ll_index] == l->id && state->c != NFA_SKIP)
4408  {
4409  /* This state is already in the list, don't add it again,
4410  * unless it is an MOPEN that is used for a backreference or
4411  * when there is a PIM. For NFA_MATCH check the position,
4412  * lower position is preferred. */
4413  if (!rex.nfa_has_backref && pim == NULL && !l->has_pim
4414  && state->c != NFA_MATCH)
4415  {
4416  /* When called from addstate_here() do insert before
4417  * existing states. */
4418  if (add_here)
4419  {
4420  for (k = 0; k < l->n && k < listindex; ++k)
4421  if (l->t[k].state->id == state->id)
4422  {
4423  found = TRUE;
4424  break;
4425  }
4426  }
4427  if (!add_here || found)
4428  {
4429 skip_add:
4430 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
4431  nfa_set_code(state->c);
4432  fprintf(log_fd, "> Not adding state %d to list %d. char %d: %s pim: %s has_pim: %d found: %d\n",
4433  abs(state->id), l->id, state->c, code,
4434  pim == NULL ? "NULL" : "yes", l->has_pim, found);
4435 #endif
4436  --depth;
4437  return subs;
4438  }
4439  }
4440 
4441  /* Do not add the state again when it exists with the same
4442  * positions. */
4443  if (has_state_with_pos(l, state, subs, pim))
4444  goto skip_add;
4445  }
4446 
4447  // When there are backreferences or PIMs the number of states may
4448  // be (a lot) bigger than anticipated.
4449  if (l->n == l->len)
4450  {
4451  int newlen = l->len * 3 / 2 + 50;
4452  size_t newsize = newlen * sizeof(nfa_thread_T);
4453  nfa_thread_T *newt;
4454 
4455  if ((long)(newsize >> 10) >= p_mmp)
4456  {
4457  emsg(_(e_maxmempat));
4458  --depth;
4459  return NULL;
4460  }
4461  if (subs != &temp_subs)
4462  {
4463  /* "subs" may point into the current array, need to make a
4464  * copy before it becomes invalid. */
4465  copy_sub(&temp_subs.norm, &subs->norm);
4466 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
4467  if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr)
4468  copy_sub(&temp_subs.synt, &subs->synt);
4469 #endif
4470  subs = &temp_subs;
4471  }
4472 
4473  newt = vim_realloc(l->t, newsize);
4474  if (newt == NULL)
4475  {
4476  // out of memory
4477  --depth;
4478  return NULL;
4479  }
4480  l->t = newt;
4481  l->len = newlen;
4482  }
4483 
4484  /* add the state to the list */
4485  state->lastlist[nfa_ll_index] = l->id;
4486  thread = &l->t[l->n++];
4487  thread->state = state;
4488  if (pim == NULL)
4489  thread->pim.result = NFA_PIM_UNUSED;
4490  else
4491  {
4492  copy_pim(&thread->pim, pim);
4493  l->has_pim = TRUE;
4494  }
4495  copy_sub(&thread->subs.norm, &subs->norm);
4496 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
4497  if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr)
4498  copy_sub(&thread->subs.synt, &subs->synt);
4499 #endif
4500 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
4501  report_state("Adding", &thread->subs.norm, state, l->id, pim);
4502  did_print = TRUE;
4503 #endif
4504  }
4505 
4506 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
4507  if (!did_print)
4508  report_state("Processing", &subs->norm, state, l->id, pim);
4509 #endif
4510  switch (state->c)
4511  {
4512  case NFA_MATCH:
4513  break;
4514 
4515  case NFA_SPLIT:
4516  /* order matters here */
4517  subs = addstate(l, state->out, subs, pim, off_arg);
4518  subs = addstate(l, state->out1, subs, pim, off_arg);
4519  break;
4520 
4521  case NFA_EMPTY:
4522  case NFA_NOPEN:
4523  case NFA_NCLOSE:
4524  subs = addstate(l, state->out, subs, pim, off_arg);
4525  break;
4526 
4527  case NFA_MOPEN:
4528  case NFA_MOPEN1:
4529  case NFA_MOPEN2:
4530  case NFA_MOPEN3:
4531  case NFA_MOPEN4:
4532  case NFA_MOPEN5:
4533  case NFA_MOPEN6:
4534  case NFA_MOPEN7:
4535  case NFA_MOPEN8:
4536  case NFA_MOPEN9:
4537 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
4538  case NFA_ZOPEN:
4539  case NFA_ZOPEN1:
4540  case NFA_ZOPEN2:
4541  case NFA_ZOPEN3:
4542  case NFA_ZOPEN4:
4543  case NFA_ZOPEN5:
4544  case NFA_ZOPEN6:
4545  case NFA_ZOPEN7:
4546  case NFA_ZOPEN8:
4547  case NFA_ZOPEN9:
4548 #endif
4549  case NFA_ZSTART:
4550  if (state->c == NFA_ZSTART)
4551  {
4552  subidx = 0;
4553  sub = &subs->norm;
4554  }
4555 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
4556  else if (state->c >= NFA_ZOPEN && state->c <= NFA_ZOPEN9)
4557  {
4558  subidx = state->c - NFA_ZOPEN;
4559  sub = &subs->synt;
4560  }
4561 #endif
4562  else
4563  {
4564  subidx = state->c - NFA_MOPEN;
4565  sub = &subs->norm;
4566  }
4567 
4568  /* avoid compiler warnings */
4569  save_ptr = NULL;
4570  vim_memset(&save_multipos, 0, sizeof(save_multipos));
4571 
4572  /* Set the position (with "off" added) in the subexpression. Save
4573  * and restore it when it was in use. Otherwise fill any gap. */
4574  if (REG_MULTI)
4575  {
4576  if (subidx < sub->in_use)
4577  {
4578  save_multipos = sub->list.multi[subidx];
4579  save_in_use = -1;
4580  }
4581  else
4582  {
4583  save_in_use = sub->in_use;
4584  for (i = sub->in_use; i < subidx; ++i)
4585  {
4586  sub->list.multi[i].start_lnum = -1;
4587  sub->list.multi[i].end_lnum = -1;
4588  }
4589  sub->in_use = subidx + 1;
4590  }
4591  if (off == -1)
4592  {
4593  sub->list.multi[subidx].start_lnum = rex.lnum + 1;
4594  sub->list.multi[subidx].start_col = 0;
4595  }
4596  else
4597  {
4598  sub->list.multi[subidx].start_lnum = rex.lnum;
4599  sub->list.multi[subidx].start_col =
4600  (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line + off);
4601  }
4602  sub->list.multi[subidx].end_lnum = -1;
4603  }
4604  else
4605  {
4606  if (subidx < sub->in_use)
4607  {
4608  save_ptr = sub->list.line[subidx].start;
4609  save_in_use = -1;
4610  }
4611  else
4612  {
4613  save_in_use = sub->in_use;
4614  for (i = sub->in_use; i < subidx; ++i)
4615  {
4616  sub->list.line[i].start = NULL;
4617  sub->list.line[i].end = NULL;
4618  }
4619  sub->in_use = subidx + 1;
4620  }
4621  sub->list.line[subidx].start = rex.input + off;
4622  }
4623 
4624  subs = addstate(l, state->out, subs, pim, off_arg);
4625  if (subs == NULL)
4626  break;
4627  // "subs" may have changed, need to set "sub" again
4628 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
4629  if (state->c >= NFA_ZOPEN && state->c <= NFA_ZOPEN9)
4630  sub = &subs->synt;
4631  else
4632 #endif
4633  sub = &subs->norm;
4634 
4635  if (save_in_use == -1)
4636  {
4637  if (REG_MULTI)
4638  sub->list.multi[subidx] = save_multipos;
4639  else
4640  sub->list.line[subidx].start = save_ptr;
4641  }
4642  else
4643  sub->in_use = save_in_use;
4644  break;
4645 
4646  case NFA_MCLOSE:
4647  if (rex.nfa_has_zend && (REG_MULTI
4648  ? subs->norm.list.multi[0].end_lnum >= 0
4649  : subs->norm.list.line[0].end != NULL))
4650  {
4651  // Do not overwrite the position set by \ze.
4652  subs = addstate(l, state->out, subs, pim, off_arg);
4653  break;
4654  }
4655  /* FALLTHROUGH */
4656  case NFA_MCLOSE1:
4657  case NFA_MCLOSE2:
4658  case NFA_MCLOSE3:
4659  case NFA_MCLOSE4:
4660  case NFA_MCLOSE5:
4661  case NFA_MCLOSE6:
4662  case NFA_MCLOSE7:
4663  case NFA_MCLOSE8:
4664  case NFA_MCLOSE9:
4665 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
4666  case NFA_ZCLOSE:
4667  case NFA_ZCLOSE1:
4668  case NFA_ZCLOSE2:
4669  case NFA_ZCLOSE3:
4670  case NFA_ZCLOSE4:
4671  case NFA_ZCLOSE5:
4672  case NFA_ZCLOSE6:
4673  case NFA_ZCLOSE7:
4674  case NFA_ZCLOSE8:
4675  case NFA_ZCLOSE9:
4676 #endif
4677  case NFA_ZEND:
4678  if (state->c == NFA_ZEND)
4679  {
4680  subidx = 0;
4681  sub = &subs->norm;
4682  }
4683 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
4684  else if (state->c >= NFA_ZCLOSE && state->c <= NFA_ZCLOSE9)
4685  {
4686  subidx = state->c - NFA_ZCLOSE;
4687  sub = &subs->synt;
4688  }
4689 #endif
4690  else
4691  {
4692  subidx = state->c - NFA_MCLOSE;
4693  sub = &subs->norm;
4694  }
4695 
4696  /* We don't fill in gaps here, there must have been an MOPEN that
4697  * has done that. */
4698  save_in_use = sub->in_use;
4699  if (sub->in_use <= subidx)
4700  sub->in_use = subidx + 1;
4701  if (REG_MULTI)
4702  {
4703  save_multipos = sub->list.multi[subidx];
4704  if (off == -1)
4705  {
4706  sub->list.multi[subidx].end_lnum = rex.lnum + 1;
4707  sub->list.multi[subidx].end_col = 0;
4708  }
4709  else
4710  {
4711  sub->list.multi[subidx].end_lnum = rex.lnum;
4712  sub->list.multi[subidx].end_col =
4713  (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line + off);
4714  }
4715  /* avoid compiler warnings */
4716  save_ptr = NULL;
4717  }
4718  else
4719  {
4720  save_ptr = sub->list.line[subidx].end;
4721  sub->list.line[subidx].end = rex.input + off;
4722  /* avoid compiler warnings */
4723  vim_memset(&save_multipos, 0, sizeof(save_multipos));
4724  }
4725 
4726  subs = addstate(l, state->out, subs, pim, off_arg);
4727  if (subs == NULL)
4728  break;
4729  /* "subs" may have changed, need to set "sub" again */
4730 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
4731  if (state->c >= NFA_ZCLOSE && state->c <= NFA_ZCLOSE9)
4732  sub = &subs->synt;
4733  else
4734 #endif
4735  sub = &subs->norm;
4736 
4737  if (REG_MULTI)
4738  sub->list.multi[subidx] = save_multipos;
4739  else
4740  sub->list.line[subidx].end = save_ptr;
4741  sub->in_use = save_in_use;
4742  break;
4743  }
4744  --depth;
4745  return subs;
4746 }
4747 
4748 /*
4749  * Like addstate(), but the new state(s) are put at position "*ip".
4750  * Used for zero-width matches, next state to use is the added one.
4751  * This makes sure the order of states to be tried does not change, which
4752  * matters for alternatives.
4753  */
4754  static regsubs_T *
4755 addstate_here(
4756  nfa_list_T *l, /* runtime state list */
4757  nfa_state_T *state, /* state to update */
4758  regsubs_T *subs, /* pointers to subexpressions */
4759  nfa_pim_T *pim, /* postponed look-behind match */
4760  int *ip)
4761 {
4762  int tlen = l->n;
4763  int count;
4764  int listidx = *ip;
4765  regsubs_T *r;
4766 
4767  /* First add the state(s) at the end, so that we know how many there are.
4768  * Pass the listidx as offset (avoids adding another argument to
4769  * addstate(). */
4770  r = addstate(l, state, subs, pim, -listidx - ADDSTATE_HERE_OFFSET);
4771  if (r == NULL)
4772  return NULL;
4773 
4774  // when "*ip" was at the end of the list, nothing to do
4775  if (listidx + 1 == tlen)
4776  return r;
4777 
4778  // re-order to put the new state at the current position
4779  count = l->n - tlen;
4780  if (count == 0)
4781  return r; // no state got added
4782  if (count == 1)
4783  {
4784  // overwrite the current state
4785  l->t[listidx] = l->t[l->n - 1];
4786  }
4787  else if (count > 1)
4788  {
4789  if (l->n + count - 1 >= l->len)
4790  {
4791  /* not enough space to move the new states, reallocate the list
4792  * and move the states to the right position */
4793  int newlen = l->len * 3 / 2 + 50;
4794  size_t newsize = newlen * sizeof(nfa_thread_T);
4795  nfa_thread_T *newl;
4796 
4797  if ((long)(newsize >> 10) >= p_mmp)
4798  {
4799  emsg(_(e_maxmempat));
4800  return NULL;
4801  }
4802  newl = alloc(newsize);
4803  if (newl == NULL)
4804  return NULL;
4805  l->len = newlen;
4806  mch_memmove(&(newl[0]),
4807  &(l->t[0]),
4808  sizeof(nfa_thread_T) * listidx);
4809  mch_memmove(&(newl[listidx]),
4810  &(l->t[l->n - count]),
4811  sizeof(nfa_thread_T) * count);
4812  mch_memmove(&(newl[listidx + count]),
4813  &(l->t[listidx + 1]),
4814  sizeof(nfa_thread_T) * (l->n - count - listidx - 1));
4815  vim_free(l->t);
4816  l->t = newl;
4817  }
4818  else
4819  {
4820  /* make space for new states, then move them from the
4821  * end to the current position */
4822  mch_memmove(&(l->t[listidx + count]),
4823  &(l->t[listidx + 1]),
4824  sizeof(nfa_thread_T) * (l->n - listidx - 1));
4825  mch_memmove(&(l->t[listidx]),
4826  &(l->t[l->n - 1]),
4827  sizeof(nfa_thread_T) * count);
4828  }
4829  }
4830  --l->n;
4831  *ip = listidx - 1;
4832 
4833  return r;
4834 }
4835 
4836 /*
4837  * Check character class "class" against current character c.
4838  */
4839  static int
4840 check_char_class(int class, int c)
4841 {
4842  switch (class)
4843  {
4844  case NFA_CLASS_ALNUM:
4845  if (c >= 1 && c < 128 && isalnum(c))
4846  return OK;
4847  break;
4848  case NFA_CLASS_ALPHA:
4849  if (c >= 1 && c < 128 && isalpha(c))
4850  return OK;
4851  break;
4852  case NFA_CLASS_BLANK:
4853  if (c == ' ' || c == '\t')
4854  return OK;
4855  break;
4856  case NFA_CLASS_CNTRL:
4857  if (c >= 1 && c <= 127 && iscntrl(c))
4858  return OK;
4859  break;
4860  case NFA_CLASS_DIGIT:
4861  if (VIM_ISDIGIT(c))
4862  return OK;
4863  break;
4864  case NFA_CLASS_GRAPH:
4865  if (c >= 1 && c <= 127 && isgraph(c))
4866  return OK;
4867  break;
4868  case NFA_CLASS_LOWER:
4869  if (MB_ISLOWER(c) && c != 170 && c != 186)
4870  return OK;
4871  break;
4872  case NFA_CLASS_PRINT:
4873  if (vim_isprintc(c))
4874  return OK;
4875  break;
4876  case NFA_CLASS_PUNCT:
4877  if (c >= 1 && c < 128 && ispunct(c))
4878  return OK;
4879  break;
4880  case NFA_CLASS_SPACE:
4881  if ((c >= 9 && c <= 13) || (c == ' '))
4882  return OK;
4883  break;
4884  case NFA_CLASS_UPPER:
4885  if (MB_ISUPPER(c))
4886  return OK;
4887  break;
4888  case NFA_CLASS_XDIGIT:
4889  if (vim_isxdigit(c))
4890  return OK;
4891  break;
4892  case NFA_CLASS_TAB:
4893  if (c == '\t')
4894  return OK;
4895  break;
4896  case NFA_CLASS_RETURN:
4897  if (c == '\r')
4898  return OK;
4899  break;
4900  case NFA_CLASS_BACKSPACE:
4901  if (c == '\b')
4902  return OK;
4903  break;
4904  case NFA_CLASS_ESCAPE:
4905  if (c == '\033')
4906  return OK;
4907  break;
4908  case NFA_CLASS_IDENT:
4909  if (vim_isIDc(c))
4910  return OK;
4911  break;
4912  case NFA_CLASS_KEYWORD:
4913  if (reg_iswordc(c))
4914  return OK;
4915  break;
4916  case NFA_CLASS_FNAME:
4917  if (vim_isfilec(c))
4918  return OK;
4919  break;
4920 
4921  default:
4922  /* should not be here :P */
4923  siemsg(_(e_ill_char_class), class);
4924  return FAIL;
4925  }
4926  return FAIL;
4927 }
4928 
4929 /*
4930  * Check for a match with subexpression "subidx".
4931  * Return TRUE if it matches.
4932  */
4933  static int
4934 match_backref(
4935  regsub_T *sub, /* pointers to subexpressions */
4936  int subidx,
4937  int *bytelen) /* out: length of match in bytes */
4938 {
4939  int len;
4940 
4941  if (sub->in_use <= subidx)
4942  {
4943 retempty:
4944  /* backref was not set, match an empty string */
4945  *bytelen = 0;
4946  return TRUE;
4947  }
4948 
4949  if (REG_MULTI)
4950  {
4951  if (sub->list.multi[subidx].start_lnum < 0
4952  || sub->list.multi[subidx].end_lnum < 0)
4953  goto retempty;
4954  if (sub->list.multi[subidx].start_lnum == rex.lnum
4955  && sub->list.multi[subidx].end_lnum == rex.lnum)
4956  {
4957  len = sub->list.multi[subidx].end_col
4958  - sub->list.multi[subidx].start_col;
4959  if (cstrncmp(rex.line + sub->list.multi[subidx].start_col,
4960  rex.input, &len) == 0)
4961  {
4962  *bytelen = len;
4963  return TRUE;
4964  }
4965  }
4966  else
4967  {
4968  if (match_with_backref(
4969  sub->list.multi[subidx].start_lnum,
4970  sub->list.multi[subidx].start_col,
4971  sub->list.multi[subidx].end_lnum,
4972  sub->list.multi[subidx].end_col,
4973  bytelen) == RA_MATCH)
4974  return TRUE;
4975  }
4976  }
4977  else
4978  {
4979  if (sub->list.line[subidx].start == NULL
4980  || sub->list.line[subidx].end == NULL)
4981  goto retempty;
4982  len = (int)(sub->list.line[subidx].end - sub->list.line[subidx].start);
4983  if (cstrncmp(sub->list.line[subidx].start, rex.input, &len) == 0)
4984  {
4985  *bytelen = len;
4986  return TRUE;
4987  }
4988  }
4989  return FALSE;
4990 }
4991 
4992 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
4993 
4994 /*
4995  * Check for a match with \z subexpression "subidx".
4996  * Return TRUE if it matches.
4997  */
4998  static int
4999 match_zref(
5000  int subidx,
5001  int *bytelen) /* out: length of match in bytes */
5002 {
5003  int len;
5004 
5005  cleanup_zsubexpr();
5006  if (re_extmatch_in == NULL || re_extmatch_in->matches[subidx] == NULL)
5007  {
5008  /* backref was not set, match an empty string */
5009  *bytelen = 0;
5010  return TRUE;
5011  }
5012 
5013  len = (int)STRLEN(re_extmatch_in->matches[subidx]);
5014  if (cstrncmp(re_extmatch_in->matches[subidx], rex.input, &len) == 0)
5015  {
5016  *bytelen = len;
5017  return TRUE;
5018  }
5019  return FALSE;
5020 }
5021 #endif
5022 
5023 /*
5024  * Save list IDs for all NFA states of "prog" into "list".
5025  * Also reset the IDs to zero.
5026  * Only used for the recursive value lastlist[1].
5027  */
5028  static void
5029 nfa_save_listids(nfa_regprog_T *prog, int *list)
5030 {
5031  int i;
5032  nfa_state_T *p;
5033 
5034  /* Order in the list is reverse, it's a bit faster that way. */
5035  p = &prog->state[0];
5036  for (i = prog->nstate; --i >= 0; )
5037  {
5038  list[i] = p->lastlist[1];
5039  p->lastlist[1] = 0;
5040  ++p;
5041  }
5042 }
5043 
5044 /*
5045  * Restore list IDs from "list" to all NFA states.
5046  */
5047  static void
5048 nfa_restore_listids(nfa_regprog_T *prog, int *list)
5049 {
5050  int i;
5051  nfa_state_T *p;
5052 
5053  p = &prog->state[0];
5054  for (i = prog->nstate; --i >= 0; )
5055  {
5056  p->lastlist[1] = list[i];
5057  ++p;
5058  }
5059 }
5060 
5061  static int
5062 nfa_re_num_cmp(long_u val, int op, long_u pos)
5063 {
5064  if (op == 1) return pos > val;
5065  if (op == 2) return pos < val;
5066  return val == pos;
5067 }
5068 
5069 static int nfa_regmatch(nfa_regprog_T *prog, nfa_state_T *start, regsubs_T *submatch, regsubs_T *m);
5070 
5071 /*
5072  * Recursively call nfa_regmatch()
5073  * "pim" is NULL or contains info about a Postponed Invisible Match (start
5074  * position).
5075  */
5076  static int
5077 recursive_regmatch(
5078  nfa_state_T *state,
5079  nfa_pim_T *pim,
5080  nfa_regprog_T *prog,
5081  regsubs_T *submatch,
5082  regsubs_T *m,
5083  int **listids,
5084  int *listids_len)
5085 {
5086  int save_reginput_col = (int)(rex.input - rex.line);
5087  int save_reglnum = rex.lnum;
5088  int save_nfa_match = nfa_match;
5089  int save_nfa_listid = rex.nfa_listid;
5090  save_se_T *save_nfa_endp = nfa_endp;
5091  save_se_T endpos;
5092  save_se_T *endposp = NULL;
5093  int result;
5094  int need_restore = FALSE;
5095 
5096  if (pim != NULL)
5097  {
5098  /* start at the position where the postponed match was */
5099  if (REG_MULTI)
5100  rex.input = rex.line + pim->end.pos.col;
5101  else
5102  rex.input = pim->end.ptr;
5103  }
5104 
5105  if (state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE
5106  || state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_FIRST
5107  || state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG
5108  || state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST)
5109  {
5110  /* The recursive match must end at the current position. When "pim" is
5111  * not NULL it specifies the current position. */
5112  endposp = &endpos;
5113  if (REG_MULTI)
5114  {
5115  if (pim == NULL)
5116  {
5117  endpos.se_u.pos.col = (int)(rex.input - rex.line);
5118  endpos.se_u.pos.lnum = rex.lnum;
5119  }
5120  else
5121  endpos.se_u.pos = pim->end.pos;
5122  }
5123  else
5124  {
5125  if (pim == NULL)
5126  endpos.se_u.ptr = rex.input;
5127  else
5128  endpos.se_u.ptr = pim->end.ptr;
5129  }
5130 
5131  /* Go back the specified number of bytes, or as far as the
5132  * start of the previous line, to try matching "\@<=" or
5133  * not matching "\@<!". This is very inefficient, limit the number of
5134  * bytes if possible. */
5135  if (state->val <= 0)
5136  {
5137  if (REG_MULTI)
5138  {
5139  rex.line = reg_getline(--rex.lnum);
5140  if (rex.line == NULL)
5141  /* can't go before the first line */
5142  rex.line = reg_getline(++rex.lnum);
5143  }
5144  rex.input = rex.line;
5145  }
5146  else
5147  {
5148  if (REG_MULTI && (int)(rex.input - rex.line) < state->val)
5149  {
5150  /* Not enough bytes in this line, go to end of
5151  * previous line. */
5152  rex.line = reg_getline(--rex.lnum);
5153  if (rex.line == NULL)
5154  {
5155  /* can't go before the first line */
5156  rex.line = reg_getline(++rex.lnum);
5157  rex.input = rex.line;
5158  }
5159  else
5160  rex.input = rex.line + STRLEN(rex.line);
5161  }
5162  if ((int)(rex.input - rex.line) >= state->val)
5163  {
5164  rex.input -= state->val;
5165  if (has_mbyte)
5166  rex.input -= mb_head_off(rex.line, rex.input);
5167  }
5168  else
5169  rex.input = rex.line;
5170  }
5171  }
5172 
5173 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5174  if (log_fd != stderr)
5175  fclose(log_fd);
5176  log_fd = NULL;
5177 #endif
5178  /* Have to clear the lastlist field of the NFA nodes, so that
5179  * nfa_regmatch() and addstate() can run properly after recursion. */
5180  if (nfa_ll_index == 1)
5181  {
5182  /* Already calling nfa_regmatch() recursively. Save the lastlist[1]
5183  * values and clear them. */
5184  if (*listids == NULL || *listids_len < prog->nstate)
5185  {
5186  vim_free(*listids);
5187  *listids = ALLOC_MULT(int, prog->nstate);
5188  if (*listids == NULL)
5189  {
5190  emsg(_("E878: (NFA) Could not allocate memory for branch traversal!"));
5191  return 0;
5192  }
5193  *listids_len = prog->nstate;
5194  }
5195  nfa_save_listids(prog, *listids);
5196  need_restore = TRUE;
5197  /* any value of rex.nfa_listid will do */
5198  }
5199  else
5200  {
5201  /* First recursive nfa_regmatch() call, switch to the second lastlist
5202  * entry. Make sure rex.nfa_listid is different from a previous
5203  * recursive call, because some states may still have this ID. */
5204  ++nfa_ll_index;
5205  if (rex.nfa_listid <= rex.nfa_alt_listid)
5206  rex.nfa_listid = rex.nfa_alt_listid;
5207  }
5208 
5209  /* Call nfa_regmatch() to check if the current concat matches at this
5210  * position. The concat ends with the node NFA_END_INVISIBLE */
5211  nfa_endp = endposp;
5212  result = nfa_regmatch(prog, state->out, submatch, m);
5213 
5214  if (need_restore)
5215  nfa_restore_listids(prog, *listids);
5216  else
5217  {
5218  --nfa_ll_index;
5219  rex.nfa_alt_listid = rex.nfa_listid;
5220  }
5221 
5222  /* restore position in input text */
5223  rex.lnum = save_reglnum;
5224  if (REG_MULTI)
5225  rex.line = reg_getline(rex.lnum);
5226  rex.input = rex.line + save_reginput_col;
5227  if (result != NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE)
5228  {
5229  nfa_match = save_nfa_match;
5230  rex.nfa_listid = save_nfa_listid;
5231  }
5232  nfa_endp = save_nfa_endp;
5233 
5234 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5235  log_fd = fopen(NFA_REGEXP_RUN_LOG, "a");
5236  if (log_fd != NULL)
5237  {
5238  fprintf(log_fd, "****************************\n");
5239  fprintf(log_fd, "FINISHED RUNNING nfa_regmatch() recursively\n");
5240  fprintf(log_fd, "MATCH = %s\n", result == TRUE ? "OK" : "FALSE");
5241  fprintf(log_fd, "****************************\n");
5242  }
5243  else
5244  {
5245  emsg(_(e_log_open_failed));
5246  log_fd = stderr;
5247  }
5248 #endif
5249 
5250  return result;
5251 }
5252 
5253 /*
5254  * Estimate the chance of a match with "state" failing.
5255  * empty match: 0
5256  * NFA_ANY: 1
5257  * specific character: 99
5258  */
5259  static int
5260 failure_chance(nfa_state_T *state, int depth)
5261 {
5262  int c = state->c;
5263  int l, r;
5264 
5265  /* detect looping */
5266  if (depth > 4)
5267  return 1;
5268 
5269  switch (c)
5270  {
5271  case NFA_SPLIT:
5272  if (state->out->c == NFA_SPLIT || state->out1->c == NFA_SPLIT)
5273  /* avoid recursive stuff */
5274  return 1;
5275  /* two alternatives, use the lowest failure chance */
5276  l = failure_chance(state->out, depth + 1);
5277  r = failure_chance(state->out1, depth + 1);
5278  return l < r ? l : r;
5279 
5280  case NFA_ANY:
5281  /* matches anything, unlikely to fail */
5282  return 1;
5283 
5284  case NFA_MATCH:
5285  case NFA_MCLOSE:
5286  case NFA_ANY_COMPOSING:
5287  /* empty match works always */
5288  return 0;
5289 
5290  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE:
5291  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_FIRST:
5292  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG:
5293  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG_FIRST:
5294  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE:
5295  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_FIRST:
5296  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG:
5297  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST:
5298  case NFA_START_PATTERN:
5299  /* recursive regmatch is expensive, use low failure chance */
5300  return 5;
5301 
5302  case NFA_BOL:
5303  case NFA_EOL:
5304  case NFA_BOF:
5305  case NFA_EOF:
5306  case NFA_NEWL:
5307  return 99;
5308 
5309  case NFA_BOW:
5310  case NFA_EOW:
5311  return 90;
5312 
5313  case NFA_MOPEN:
5314  case NFA_MOPEN1:
5315  case NFA_MOPEN2:
5316  case NFA_MOPEN3:
5317  case NFA_MOPEN4:
5318  case NFA_MOPEN5:
5319  case NFA_MOPEN6:
5320  case NFA_MOPEN7:
5321  case NFA_MOPEN8:
5322  case NFA_MOPEN9:
5323 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
5324  case NFA_ZOPEN:
5325  case NFA_ZOPEN1:
5326  case NFA_ZOPEN2:
5327  case NFA_ZOPEN3:
5328  case NFA_ZOPEN4:
5329  case NFA_ZOPEN5:
5330  case NFA_ZOPEN6:
5331  case NFA_ZOPEN7:
5332  case NFA_ZOPEN8:
5333  case NFA_ZOPEN9:
5334  case NFA_ZCLOSE:
5335  case NFA_ZCLOSE1:
5336  case NFA_ZCLOSE2:
5337  case NFA_ZCLOSE3:
5338  case NFA_ZCLOSE4:
5339  case NFA_ZCLOSE5:
5340  case NFA_ZCLOSE6:
5341  case NFA_ZCLOSE7:
5342  case NFA_ZCLOSE8:
5343  case NFA_ZCLOSE9:
5344 #endif
5345  case NFA_NOPEN:
5346  case NFA_MCLOSE1:
5347  case NFA_MCLOSE2:
5348  case NFA_MCLOSE3:
5349  case NFA_MCLOSE4:
5350  case NFA_MCLOSE5:
5351  case NFA_MCLOSE6:
5352  case NFA_MCLOSE7:
5353  case NFA_MCLOSE8:
5354  case NFA_MCLOSE9:
5355  case NFA_NCLOSE:
5356  return failure_chance(state->out, depth + 1);
5357 
5358  case NFA_BACKREF1:
5359  case NFA_BACKREF2:
5360  case NFA_BACKREF3:
5361  case NFA_BACKREF4:
5362  case NFA_BACKREF5:
5363  case NFA_BACKREF6:
5364  case NFA_BACKREF7:
5365  case NFA_BACKREF8:
5366  case NFA_BACKREF9:
5367 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
5368  case NFA_ZREF1:
5369  case NFA_ZREF2:
5370  case NFA_ZREF3:
5371  case NFA_ZREF4:
5372  case NFA_ZREF5:
5373  case NFA_ZREF6:
5374  case NFA_ZREF7:
5375  case NFA_ZREF8:
5376  case NFA_ZREF9:
5377 #endif
5378  /* backreferences don't match in many places */
5379  return 94;
5380 
5381  case NFA_LNUM_GT:
5382  case NFA_LNUM_LT:
5383  case NFA_COL_GT:
5384  case NFA_COL_LT:
5385  case NFA_VCOL_GT:
5386  case NFA_VCOL_LT:
5387  case NFA_MARK_GT:
5388  case NFA_MARK_LT:
5389  case NFA_VISUAL:
5390  /* before/after positions don't match very often */
5391  return 85;
5392 
5393  case NFA_LNUM:
5394  return 90;
5395 
5396  case NFA_CURSOR:
5397  case NFA_COL:
5398  case NFA_VCOL:
5399  case NFA_MARK:
5400  /* specific positions rarely match */
5401  return 98;
5402 
5403  case NFA_COMPOSING:
5404  return 95;
5405 
5406  default:
5407  if (c > 0)
5408  /* character match fails often */
5409  return 95;
5410  }
5411 
5412  /* something else, includes character classes */
5413  return 50;
5414 }
5415 
5416 /*
5417  * Skip until the char "c" we know a match must start with.
5418  */
5419  static int
5420 skip_to_start(int c, colnr_T *colp)
5421 {
5422  char_u *s;
5423 
5424  /* Used often, do some work to avoid call overhead. */
5425  if (!rex.reg_ic && !has_mbyte)
5426  s = vim_strbyte(rex.line + *colp, c);
5427  else
5428  s = cstrchr(rex.line + *colp, c);
5429  if (s == NULL)
5430  return FAIL;
5431  *colp = (int)(s - rex.line);
5432  return OK;
5433 }
5434 
5435 /*
5436  * Check for a match with match_text.
5437  * Called after skip_to_start() has found regstart.
5438  * Returns zero for no match, 1 for a match.
5439  */
5440  static long
5441 find_match_text(colnr_T startcol, int regstart, char_u *match_text)
5442 {
5443  colnr_T col = startcol;
5444  int c1, c2;
5445  int len1, len2;
5446  int match;
5447 
5448  for (;;)
5449  {
5450  match = TRUE;
5451  len2 = MB_CHAR2LEN(regstart); /* skip regstart */
5452  for (len1 = 0; match_text[len1] != NUL; len1 += MB_CHAR2LEN(c1))
5453  {
5454  c1 = PTR2CHAR(match_text + len1);
5455  c2 = PTR2CHAR(rex.line + col + len2);
5456  if (c1 != c2 && (!rex.reg_ic || MB_TOLOWER(c1) != MB_TOLOWER(c2)))
5457  {
5458  match = FALSE;
5459  break;
5460  }
5461  len2 += MB_CHAR2LEN(c2);
5462  }
5463  if (match
5464  /* check that no composing char follows */
5465  && !(enc_utf8
5466  && utf_iscomposing(PTR2CHAR(rex.line + col + len2))))
5467  {
5468  cleanup_subexpr();
5469  if (REG_MULTI)
5470  {
5471  rex.reg_startpos[0].lnum = rex.lnum;
5472  rex.reg_startpos[0].col = col;
5473  rex.reg_endpos[0].lnum = rex.lnum;
5474  rex.reg_endpos[0].col = col + len2;
5475  }
5476  else
5477  {
5478  rex.reg_startp[0] = rex.line + col;
5479  rex.reg_endp[0] = rex.line + col + len2;
5480  }
5481  return 1L;
5482  }
5483 
5484  /* Try finding regstart after the current match. */
5485  col += MB_CHAR2LEN(regstart); /* skip regstart */
5486  if (skip_to_start(regstart, &col) == FAIL)
5487  break;
5488  }
5489  return 0L;
5490 }
5491 
5492 #ifdef FEAT_RELTIME
5493  static int
5494 nfa_did_time_out()
5495 {
5496  if (nfa_time_limit != NULL && profile_passed_limit(nfa_time_limit))
5497  {
5498  if (nfa_timed_out != NULL)
5499  *nfa_timed_out = TRUE;
5500  return TRUE;
5501  }
5502  return FALSE;
5503 }
5504 #endif
5505 
5506 /*
5507  * Main matching routine.
5508  *
5509  * Run NFA to determine whether it matches rex.input.
5510  *
5511  * When "nfa_endp" is not NULL it is a required end-of-match position.
5512  *
5513  * Return TRUE if there is a match, FALSE if there is no match,
5514  * NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE if we end up with too many states.
5515  * When there is a match "submatch" contains the positions.
5516  *
5517  * Note: Caller must ensure that: start != NULL.
5518  */
5519  static int
5520 nfa_regmatch(
5521  nfa_regprog_T *prog,
5522  nfa_state_T *start,
5523  regsubs_T *submatch,
5524  regsubs_T *m)
5525 {
5526  int result = FALSE;
5527  size_t size = 0;
5528  int flag = 0;
5529  int go_to_nextline = FALSE;
5530  nfa_thread_T *t;
5531  nfa_list_T list[2];
5532  int listidx;
5533  nfa_list_T *thislist;
5534  nfa_list_T *nextlist;
5535  int *listids = NULL;
5536  int listids_len = 0;
5537  nfa_state_T *add_state;
5538  int add_here;
5539  int add_count;
5540  int add_off = 0;
5541  int toplevel = start->c == NFA_MOPEN;
5542  regsubs_T *r;
5543 #ifdef NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG
5544  FILE *debug;
5545 #endif
5546 
5547  /* Some patterns may take a long time to match, especially when using
5548  * recursive_regmatch(). Allow interrupting them with CTRL-C. */
5549  fast_breakcheck();
5550  if (got_int)
5551  return FALSE;
5552 #ifdef FEAT_RELTIME
5553  if (nfa_did_time_out())
5554  return FALSE;
5555 #endif
5556 
5557 #ifdef NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG
5558  debug = fopen(NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG, "a");
5559  if (debug == NULL)
5560  {
5561  semsg("(NFA) COULD NOT OPEN %s!", NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG);
5562  return FALSE;
5563  }
5564 #endif
5565  nfa_match = FALSE;
5566 
5567  /* Allocate memory for the lists of nodes. */
5568  size = (prog->nstate + 1) * sizeof(nfa_thread_T);
5569 
5570  list[0].t = alloc(size);
5571  list[0].len = prog->nstate + 1;
5572  list[1].t = alloc(size);
5573  list[1].len = prog->nstate + 1;
5574  if (list[0].t == NULL || list[1].t == NULL)
5575  goto theend;
5576 
5577 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5578  log_fd = fopen(NFA_REGEXP_RUN_LOG, "a");
5579  if (log_fd != NULL)
5580  {
5581  fprintf(log_fd, "**********************************\n");
5582  nfa_set_code(start->c);
5583  fprintf(log_fd, " RUNNING nfa_regmatch() starting with state %d, code %s\n",
5584  abs(start->id), code);
5585  fprintf(log_fd, "**********************************\n");
5586  }
5587  else
5588  {
5589  emsg(_(e_log_open_failed));
5590  log_fd = stderr;
5591  }
5592 #endif
5593 
5594  thislist = &list[0];
5595  thislist->n = 0;
5596  thislist->has_pim = FALSE;
5597  nextlist = &list[1];
5598  nextlist->n = 0;
5599  nextlist->has_pim = FALSE;
5600 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5601  fprintf(log_fd, "(---) STARTSTATE first\n");
5602 #endif
5603  thislist->id = rex.nfa_listid + 1;
5604 
5605  /* Inline optimized code for addstate(thislist, start, m, 0) if we know
5606  * it's the first MOPEN. */
5607  if (toplevel)
5608  {
5609  if (REG_MULTI)
5610  {
5611  m->norm.list.multi[0].start_lnum = rex.lnum;
5612  m->norm.list.multi[0].start_col = (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line);
5613  }
5614  else
5615  m->norm.list.line[0].start = rex.input;
5616  m->norm.in_use = 1;
5617  r = addstate(thislist, start->out, m, NULL, 0);
5618  }
5619  else
5620  r = addstate(thislist, start, m, NULL, 0);
5621  if (r == NULL)
5622  {
5623  nfa_match = NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE;
5624  goto theend;
5625  }
5626 
5627 #define ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(state) \
5628  if (result) { \
5629  add_state = state->out; \
5630  add_off = clen; \
5631  }
5632 
5633  /*
5634  * Run for each character.
5635  */
5636  for (;;)
5637  {
5638  int curc;
5639  int clen;
5640 
5641  if (has_mbyte)
5642  {
5643  curc = (*mb_ptr2char)(rex.input);
5644  clen = (*mb_ptr2len)(rex.input);
5645  }
5646  else
5647  {
5648  curc = *rex.input;
5649  clen = 1;
5650  }
5651  if (curc == NUL)
5652  {
5653  clen = 0;
5654  go_to_nextline = FALSE;
5655  }
5656 
5657  /* swap lists */
5658  thislist = &list[flag];
5659  nextlist = &list[flag ^= 1];
5660  nextlist->n = 0; /* clear nextlist */
5661  nextlist->has_pim = FALSE;
5662  ++rex.nfa_listid;
5663  if (prog->re_engine == AUTOMATIC_ENGINE
5664  && (rex.nfa_listid >= NFA_MAX_STATES
5665 # ifdef FEAT_EVAL
5666  || nfa_fail_for_testing
5667 # endif
5668  ))
5669  {
5670  /* too many states, retry with old engine */
5671  nfa_match = NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE;
5672  goto theend;
5673  }
5674 
5675  thislist->id = rex.nfa_listid;
5676  nextlist->id = rex.nfa_listid + 1;
5677 
5678 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5679  fprintf(log_fd, "------------------------------------------\n");
5680  fprintf(log_fd, ">>> Reginput is \"%s\"\n", rex.input);
5681  fprintf(log_fd, ">>> Advanced one character... Current char is %c (code %d) \n", curc, (int)curc);
5682  fprintf(log_fd, ">>> Thislist has %d states available: ", thislist->n);
5683  {
5684  int i;
5685 
5686  for (i = 0; i < thislist->n; i++)
5687  fprintf(log_fd, "%d ", abs(thislist->t[i].state->id));
5688  }
5689  fprintf(log_fd, "\n");
5690 #endif
5691 
5692 #ifdef NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG
5693  fprintf(debug, "\n-------------------\n");
5694 #endif
5695  /*
5696  * If the state lists are empty we can stop.
5697  */
5698  if (thislist->n == 0)
5699  break;
5700 
5701  /* compute nextlist */
5702  for (listidx = 0; listidx < thislist->n; ++listidx)
5703  {
5704  /* If the list gets very long there probably is something wrong.
5705  * At least allow interrupting with CTRL-C. */
5706  fast_breakcheck();
5707  if (got_int)
5708  break;
5709 #ifdef FEAT_RELTIME
5710  if (nfa_time_limit != NULL && ++nfa_time_count == 20)
5711  {
5712  nfa_time_count = 0;
5713  if (nfa_did_time_out())
5714  break;
5715  }
5716 #endif
5717  t = &thislist->t[listidx];
5718 
5719 #ifdef NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG
5720  nfa_set_code(t->state->c);
5721  fprintf(debug, "%s, ", code);
5722 #endif
5723 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5724  {
5725  int col;
5726 
5727  if (t->subs.norm.in_use <= 0)
5728  col = -1;
5729  else if (REG_MULTI)
5730  col = t->subs.norm.list.multi[0].start_col;
5731  else
5732  col = (int)(t->subs.norm.list.line[0].start - rex.line);
5733  nfa_set_code(t->state->c);
5734  fprintf(log_fd, "(%d) char %d %s (start col %d)%s... \n",
5735  abs(t->state->id), (int)t->state->c, code, col,
5736  pim_info(&t->pim));
5737  }
5738 #endif
5739 
5740  /*
5741  * Handle the possible codes of the current state.
5742  * The most important is NFA_MATCH.
5743  */
5744  add_state = NULL;
5745  add_here = FALSE;
5746  add_count = 0;
5747  switch (t->state->c)
5748  {
5749  case NFA_MATCH:
5750  {
5751  /* If the match ends before a composing characters and
5752  * rex.reg_icombine is not set, that is not really a match. */
5753  if (enc_utf8 && !rex.reg_icombine && utf_iscomposing(curc))
5754  break;
5755 
5756  nfa_match = TRUE;
5757  copy_sub(&submatch->norm, &t->subs.norm);
5758 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
5759  if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr)
5760  copy_sub(&submatch->synt, &t->subs.synt);
5761 #endif
5762 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5763  log_subsexpr(&t->subs);
5764 #endif
5765  /* Found the left-most longest match, do not look at any other
5766  * states at this position. When the list of states is going
5767  * to be empty quit without advancing, so that "rex.input" is
5768  * correct. */
5769  if (nextlist->n == 0)
5770  clen = 0;
5771  goto nextchar;
5772  }
5773 
5774  case NFA_END_INVISIBLE:
5775  case NFA_END_INVISIBLE_NEG:
5776  case NFA_END_PATTERN:
5777  /*
5778  * This is only encountered after a NFA_START_INVISIBLE or
5779  * NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE node.
5780  * They surround a zero-width group, used with "\@=", "\&",
5781  * "\@!", "\@<=" and "\@<!".
5782  * If we got here, it means that the current "invisible" group
5783  * finished successfully, so return control to the parent
5784  * nfa_regmatch(). For a look-behind match only when it ends
5785  * in the position in "nfa_endp".
5786  * Submatches are stored in *m, and used in the parent call.
5787  */
5788 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5789  if (nfa_endp != NULL)
5790  {
5791  if (REG_MULTI)
5792  fprintf(log_fd, "Current lnum: %d, endp lnum: %d; current col: %d, endp col: %d\n",
5793  (int)rex.lnum,
5794  (int)nfa_endp->se_u.pos.lnum,
5795  (int)(rex.input - rex.line),
5796  nfa_endp->se_u.pos.col);
5797  else
5798  fprintf(log_fd, "Current col: %d, endp col: %d\n",
5799  (int)(rex.input - rex.line),
5800  (int)(nfa_endp->se_u.ptr - rex.input));
5801  }
5802 #endif
5803  /* If "nfa_endp" is set it's only a match if it ends at
5804  * "nfa_endp" */
5805  if (nfa_endp != NULL && (REG_MULTI
5806  ? (rex.lnum != nfa_endp->se_u.pos.lnum
5807  || (int)(rex.input - rex.line)
5808  != nfa_endp->se_u.pos.col)
5809  : rex.input != nfa_endp->se_u.ptr))
5810  break;
5811 
5812  /* do not set submatches for \@! */
5813  if (t->state->c != NFA_END_INVISIBLE_NEG)
5814  {
5815  copy_sub(&m->norm, &t->subs.norm);
5816 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
5817  if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr)
5818  copy_sub(&m->synt, &t->subs.synt);
5819 #endif
5820  }
5821 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5822  fprintf(log_fd, "Match found:\n");
5823  log_subsexpr(m);
5824 #endif
5825  nfa_match = TRUE;
5826  /* See comment above at "goto nextchar". */
5827  if (nextlist->n == 0)
5828  clen = 0;
5829  goto nextchar;
5830 
5831  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE:
5832  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_FIRST:
5833  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG:
5834  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG_FIRST:
5835  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE:
5836  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_FIRST:
5837  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG:
5838  case NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST:
5839  {
5840 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5841  fprintf(log_fd, "Failure chance invisible: %d, what follows: %d\n",
5842  failure_chance(t->state->out, 0),
5843  failure_chance(t->state->out1->out, 0));
5844 #endif
5845  /* Do it directly if there already is a PIM or when
5846  * nfa_postprocess() detected it will work better. */
5847  if (t->pim.result != NFA_PIM_UNUSED
5848  || t->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_FIRST
5849  || t->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG_FIRST
5850  || t->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_FIRST
5851  || t->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST)
5852  {
5853  int in_use = m->norm.in_use;
5854 
5855  /* Copy submatch info for the recursive call, opposite
5856  * of what happens on success below. */
5857  copy_sub_off(&m->norm, &t->subs.norm);
5858 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
5859  if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr)
5860  copy_sub_off(&m->synt, &t->subs.synt);
5861 #endif
5862 
5863  /*
5864  * First try matching the invisible match, then what
5865  * follows.
5866  */
5867  result = recursive_regmatch(t->state, NULL, prog,
5868  submatch, m, &listids, &listids_len);
5869  if (result == NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE)
5870  {
5871  nfa_match = result;
5872  goto theend;
5873  }
5874 
5875  /* for \@! and \@<! it is a match when the result is
5876  * FALSE */
5877  if (result != (t->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG
5878  || t->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG_FIRST
5879  || t->state->c
5880  == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG
5881  || t->state->c
5882  == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST))
5883  {
5884  /* Copy submatch info from the recursive call */
5885  copy_sub_off(&t->subs.norm, &m->norm);
5886 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
5887  if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr)
5888  copy_sub_off(&t->subs.synt, &m->synt);
5889 #endif
5890  /* If the pattern has \ze and it matched in the
5891  * sub pattern, use it. */
5892  copy_ze_off(&t->subs.norm, &m->norm);
5893 
5894  /* t->state->out1 is the corresponding
5895  * END_INVISIBLE node; Add its out to the current
5896  * list (zero-width match). */
5897  add_here = TRUE;
5898  add_state = t->state->out1->out;
5899  }
5900  m->norm.in_use = in_use;
5901  }
5902  else
5903  {
5904  nfa_pim_T pim;
5905 
5906  /*
5907  * First try matching what follows. Only if a match
5908  * is found verify the invisible match matches. Add a
5909  * nfa_pim_T to the following states, it contains info
5910  * about the invisible match.
5911  */
5912  pim.state = t->state;
5913  pim.result = NFA_PIM_TODO;
5914  pim.subs.norm.in_use = 0;
5915 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
5916  pim.subs.synt.in_use = 0;
5917 #endif
5918  if (REG_MULTI)
5919  {
5920  pim.end.pos.col = (int)(rex.input - rex.line);
5921  pim.end.pos.lnum = rex.lnum;
5922  }
5923  else
5924  pim.end.ptr = rex.input;
5925 
5926  /* t->state->out1 is the corresponding END_INVISIBLE
5927  * node; Add its out to the current list (zero-width
5928  * match). */
5929  if (addstate_here(thislist, t->state->out1->out,
5930  &t->subs, &pim, &listidx) == NULL)
5931  {
5932  nfa_match = NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE;
5933  goto theend;
5934  }
5935  }
5936  }
5937  break;
5938 
5939  case NFA_START_PATTERN:
5940  {
5941  nfa_state_T *skip = NULL;
5942 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5943  int skip_lid = 0;
5944 #endif
5945 
5946  /* There is no point in trying to match the pattern if the
5947  * output state is not going to be added to the list. */
5948  if (state_in_list(nextlist, t->state->out1->out, &t->subs))
5949  {
5950  skip = t->state->out1->out;
5951 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5952  skip_lid = nextlist->id;
5953 #endif
5954  }
5955  else if (state_in_list(nextlist,
5956  t->state->out1->out->out, &t->subs))
5957  {
5958  skip = t->state->out1->out->out;
5959 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5960  skip_lid = nextlist->id;
5961 #endif
5962  }
5963  else if (state_in_list(thislist,
5964  t->state->out1->out->out, &t->subs))
5965  {
5966  skip = t->state->out1->out->out;
5967 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5968  skip_lid = thislist->id;
5969 #endif
5970  }
5971  if (skip != NULL)
5972  {
5973 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
5974  nfa_set_code(skip->c);
5975  fprintf(log_fd, "> Not trying to match pattern, output state %d is already in list %d. char %d: %s\n",
5976  abs(skip->id), skip_lid, skip->c, code);
5977 #endif
5978  break;
5979  }
5980  /* Copy submatch info to the recursive call, opposite of what
5981  * happens afterwards. */
5982  copy_sub_off(&m->norm, &t->subs.norm);
5983 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
5984  if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr)
5985  copy_sub_off(&m->synt, &t->subs.synt);
5986 #endif
5987 
5988  /* First try matching the pattern. */
5989  result = recursive_regmatch(t->state, NULL, prog,
5990  submatch, m, &listids, &listids_len);
5991  if (result == NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE)
5992  {
5993  nfa_match = result;
5994  goto theend;
5995  }
5996  if (result)
5997  {
5998  int bytelen;
5999 
6000 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
6001  fprintf(log_fd, "NFA_START_PATTERN matches:\n");
6002  log_subsexpr(m);
6003 #endif
6004  /* Copy submatch info from the recursive call */
6005  copy_sub_off(&t->subs.norm, &m->norm);
6006 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
6007  if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr)
6008  copy_sub_off(&t->subs.synt, &m->synt);
6009 #endif
6010  /* Now we need to skip over the matched text and then
6011  * continue with what follows. */
6012  if (REG_MULTI)
6013  /* TODO: multi-line match */
6014  bytelen = m->norm.list.multi[0].end_col
6015  - (int)(rex.input - rex.line);
6016  else
6017  bytelen = (int)(m->norm.list.line[0].end - rex.input);
6018 
6019 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
6020  fprintf(log_fd, "NFA_START_PATTERN length: %d\n", bytelen);
6021 #endif
6022  if (bytelen == 0)
6023  {
6024  /* empty match, output of corresponding
6025  * NFA_END_PATTERN/NFA_SKIP to be used at current
6026  * position */
6027  add_here = TRUE;
6028  add_state = t->state->out1->out->out;
6029  }
6030  else if (bytelen <= clen)
6031  {
6032  /* match current character, output of corresponding
6033  * NFA_END_PATTERN to be used at next position. */
6034  add_state = t->state->out1->out->out;
6035  add_off = clen;
6036  }
6037  else
6038  {
6039  /* skip over the matched characters, set character
6040  * count in NFA_SKIP */
6041  add_state = t->state->out1->out;
6042  add_off = bytelen;
6043  add_count = bytelen - clen;
6044  }
6045  }
6046  break;
6047  }
6048 
6049  case NFA_BOL:
6050  if (rex.input == rex.line)
6051  {
6052  add_here = TRUE;
6053  add_state = t->state->out;
6054  }
6055  break;
6056 
6057  case NFA_EOL:
6058  if (curc == NUL)
6059  {
6060  add_here = TRUE;
6061  add_state = t->state->out;
6062  }
6063  break;
6064 
6065  case NFA_BOW:
6066  result = TRUE;
6067 
6068  if (curc == NUL)
6069  result = FALSE;
6070  else if (has_mbyte)
6071  {
6072  int this_class;
6073 
6074  /* Get class of current and previous char (if it exists). */
6075  this_class = mb_get_class_buf(rex.input, rex.reg_buf);
6076  if (this_class <= 1)
6077  result = FALSE;
6078  else if (reg_prev_class() == this_class)
6079  result = FALSE;
6080  }
6081  else if (!vim_iswordc_buf(curc, rex.reg_buf)
6082  || (rex.input > rex.line
6083  && vim_iswordc_buf(rex.input[-1], rex.reg_buf)))
6084  result = FALSE;
6085  if (result)
6086  {
6087  add_here = TRUE;
6088  add_state = t->state->out;
6089  }
6090  break;
6091 
6092  case NFA_EOW:
6093  result = TRUE;
6094  if (rex.input == rex.line)
6095  result = FALSE;
6096  else if (has_mbyte)
6097  {
6098  int this_class, prev_class;
6099 
6100  /* Get class of current and previous char (if it exists). */
6101  this_class = mb_get_class_buf(rex.input, rex.reg_buf);
6102  prev_class = reg_prev_class();
6103  if (this_class == prev_class
6104  || prev_class == 0 || prev_class == 1)
6105  result = FALSE;
6106  }
6107  else if (!vim_iswordc_buf(rex.input[-1], rex.reg_buf)
6108  || (rex.input[0] != NUL
6109  && vim_iswordc_buf(curc, rex.reg_buf)))
6110  result = FALSE;
6111  if (result)
6112  {
6113  add_here = TRUE;
6114  add_state = t->state->out;
6115  }
6116  break;
6117 
6118  case NFA_BOF:
6119  if (rex.lnum == 0 && rex.input == rex.line
6120  && (!REG_MULTI || rex.reg_firstlnum == 1))
6121  {
6122  add_here = TRUE;
6123  add_state = t->state->out;
6124  }
6125  break;
6126 
6127  case NFA_EOF:
6128  if (rex.lnum == rex.reg_maxline && curc == NUL)
6129  {
6130  add_here = TRUE;
6131  add_state = t->state->out;
6132  }
6133  break;
6134 
6135  case NFA_COMPOSING:
6136  {
6137  int mc = curc;
6138  int len = 0;
6139  nfa_state_T *end;
6140  nfa_state_T *sta;
6141  int cchars[MAX_MCO];
6142  int ccount = 0;
6143  int j;
6144 
6145  sta = t->state->out;
6146  len = 0;
6147  if (utf_iscomposing(sta->c))
6148  {
6149  /* Only match composing character(s), ignore base
6150  * character. Used for ".{composing}" and "{composing}"
6151  * (no preceding character). */
6152  len += mb_char2len(mc);
6153  }
6154  if (rex.reg_icombine && len == 0)
6155  {
6156  /* If \Z was present, then ignore composing characters.
6157  * When ignoring the base character this always matches. */
6158  if (sta->c != curc)
6159  result = FAIL;
6160  else
6161  result = OK;
6162  while (sta->c != NFA_END_COMPOSING)
6163  sta = sta->out;
6164  }
6165 
6166  /* Check base character matches first, unless ignored. */
6167  else if (len > 0 || mc == sta->c)
6168  {
6169  if (len == 0)
6170  {
6171  len += mb_char2len(mc);
6172  sta = sta->out;
6173  }
6174 
6175  /* We don't care about the order of composing characters.
6176  * Get them into cchars[] first. */
6177  while (len < clen)
6178  {
6179  mc = mb_ptr2char(rex.input + len);
6180  cchars[ccount++] = mc;
6181  len += mb_char2len(mc);
6182  if (ccount == MAX_MCO)
6183  break;
6184  }
6185 
6186  /* Check that each composing char in the pattern matches a
6187  * composing char in the text. We do not check if all
6188  * composing chars are matched. */
6189  result = OK;
6190  while (sta->c != NFA_END_COMPOSING)
6191  {
6192  for (j = 0; j < ccount; ++j)
6193  if (cchars[j] == sta->c)
6194  break;
6195  if (j == ccount)
6196  {
6197  result = FAIL;
6198  break;
6199  }
6200  sta = sta->out;
6201  }
6202  }
6203  else
6204  result = FAIL;
6205 
6206  end = t->state->out1; /* NFA_END_COMPOSING */
6207  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(end);
6208  break;
6209  }
6210 
6211  case NFA_NEWL:
6212  if (curc == NUL && !rex.reg_line_lbr && REG_MULTI
6213  && rex.lnum <= rex.reg_maxline)
6214  {
6215  go_to_nextline = TRUE;
6216  /* Pass -1 for the offset, which means taking the position
6217  * at the start of the next line. */
6218  add_state = t->state->out;
6219  add_off = -1;
6220  }
6221  else if (curc == '\n' && rex.reg_line_lbr)
6222  {
6223  /* match \n as if it is an ordinary character */
6224  add_state = t->state->out;
6225  add_off = 1;
6226  }
6227  break;
6228 
6229  case NFA_START_COLL:
6230  case NFA_START_NEG_COLL:
6231  {
6232  /* What follows is a list of characters, until NFA_END_COLL.
6233  * One of them must match or none of them must match. */
6234  nfa_state_T *state;
6235  int result_if_matched;
6236  int c1, c2;
6237 
6238  /* Never match EOL. If it's part of the collection it is added
6239  * as a separate state with an OR. */
6240  if (curc == NUL)
6241  break;
6242 
6243  state = t->state->out;
6244  result_if_matched = (t->state->c == NFA_START_COLL);
6245  for (;;)
6246  {
6247  if (state->c == NFA_END_COLL)
6248  {
6249  result = !result_if_matched;
6250  break;
6251  }
6252  if (state->c == NFA_RANGE_MIN)
6253  {
6254  c1 = state->val;
6255  state = state->out; /* advance to NFA_RANGE_MAX */
6256  c2 = state->val;
6257 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
6258  fprintf(log_fd, "NFA_RANGE_MIN curc=%d c1=%d c2=%d\n",
6259  curc, c1, c2);
6260 #endif
6261  if (curc >= c1 && curc <= c2)
6262  {
6263  result = result_if_matched;
6264  break;
6265  }
6266  if (rex.reg_ic)
6267  {
6268  int curc_low = MB_TOLOWER(curc);
6269  int done = FALSE;
6270 
6271  for ( ; c1 <= c2; ++c1)
6272  if (MB_TOLOWER(c1) == curc_low)
6273  {
6274  result = result_if_matched;
6275  done = TRUE;
6276  break;
6277  }
6278  if (done)
6279  break;
6280  }
6281  }
6282  else if (state->c < 0 ? check_char_class(state->c, curc)
6283  : (curc == state->c
6284  || (rex.reg_ic && MB_TOLOWER(curc)
6285  == MB_TOLOWER(state->c))))
6286  {
6287  result = result_if_matched;
6288  break;
6289  }
6290  state = state->out;
6291  }
6292  if (result)
6293  {
6294  /* next state is in out of the NFA_END_COLL, out1 of
6295  * START points to the END state */
6296  add_state = t->state->out1->out;
6297  add_off = clen;
6298  }
6299  break;
6300  }
6301 
6302  case NFA_ANY:
6303  /* Any char except '\0', (end of input) does not match. */
6304  if (curc > 0)
6305  {
6306  add_state = t->state->out;
6307  add_off = clen;
6308  }
6309  break;
6310 
6311  case NFA_ANY_COMPOSING:
6312  /* On a composing character skip over it. Otherwise do
6313  * nothing. Always matches. */
6314  if (enc_utf8 && utf_iscomposing(curc))
6315  {
6316  add_off = clen;
6317  }
6318  else
6319  {
6320  add_here = TRUE;
6321  add_off = 0;
6322  }
6323  add_state = t->state->out;
6324  break;
6325 
6326  /*
6327  * Character classes like \a for alpha, \d for digit etc.
6328  */
6329  case NFA_IDENT: /* \i */
6330  result = vim_isIDc(curc);
6331  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6332  break;
6333 
6334  case NFA_SIDENT: /* \I */
6335  result = !VIM_ISDIGIT(curc) && vim_isIDc(curc);
6336  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6337  break;
6338 
6339  case NFA_KWORD: /* \k */
6340  result = vim_iswordp_buf(rex.input, rex.reg_buf);
6341  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6342  break;
6343 
6344  case NFA_SKWORD: /* \K */
6345  result = !VIM_ISDIGIT(curc)
6346  && vim_iswordp_buf(rex.input, rex.reg_buf);
6347  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6348  break;
6349 
6350  case NFA_FNAME: /* \f */
6351  result = vim_isfilec(curc);
6352  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6353  break;
6354 
6355  case NFA_SFNAME: /* \F */
6356  result = !VIM_ISDIGIT(curc) && vim_isfilec(curc);
6357  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6358  break;
6359 
6360  case NFA_PRINT: /* \p */
6361  result = vim_isprintc(PTR2CHAR(rex.input));
6362  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6363  break;
6364 
6365  case NFA_SPRINT: /* \P */
6366  result = !VIM_ISDIGIT(curc) && vim_isprintc(PTR2CHAR(rex.input));
6367  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6368  break;
6369 
6370  case NFA_WHITE: /* \s */
6371  result = VIM_ISWHITE(curc);
6372  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6373  break;
6374 
6375  case NFA_NWHITE: /* \S */
6376  result = curc != NUL && !VIM_ISWHITE(curc);
6377  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6378  break;
6379 
6380  case NFA_DIGIT: /* \d */
6381  result = ri_digit(curc);
6382  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6383  break;
6384 
6385  case NFA_NDIGIT: /* \D */
6386  result = curc != NUL && !ri_digit(curc);
6387  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6388  break;
6389 
6390  case NFA_HEX: /* \x */
6391  result = ri_hex(curc);
6392  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6393  break;
6394 
6395  case NFA_NHEX: /* \X */
6396  result = curc != NUL && !ri_hex(curc);
6397  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6398  break;
6399 
6400  case NFA_OCTAL: /* \o */
6401  result = ri_octal(curc);
6402  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6403  break;
6404 
6405  case NFA_NOCTAL: /* \O */
6406  result = curc != NUL && !ri_octal(curc);
6407  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6408  break;
6409 
6410  case NFA_WORD: /* \w */
6411  result = ri_word(curc);
6412  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6413  break;
6414 
6415  case NFA_NWORD: /* \W */
6416  result = curc != NUL && !ri_word(curc);
6417  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6418  break;
6419 
6420  case NFA_HEAD: /* \h */
6421  result = ri_head(curc);
6422  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6423  break;
6424 
6425  case NFA_NHEAD: /* \H */
6426  result = curc != NUL && !ri_head(curc);
6427  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6428  break;
6429 
6430  case NFA_ALPHA: /* \a */
6431  result = ri_alpha(curc);
6432  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6433  break;
6434 
6435  case NFA_NALPHA: /* \A */
6436  result = curc != NUL && !ri_alpha(curc);
6437  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6438  break;
6439 
6440  case NFA_LOWER: /* \l */
6441  result = ri_lower(curc);
6442  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6443  break;
6444 
6445  case NFA_NLOWER: /* \L */
6446  result = curc != NUL && !ri_lower(curc);
6447  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6448  break;
6449 
6450  case NFA_UPPER: /* \u */
6451  result = ri_upper(curc);
6452  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6453  break;
6454 
6455  case NFA_NUPPER: /* \U */
6456  result = curc != NUL && !ri_upper(curc);
6457  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6458  break;
6459 
6460  case NFA_LOWER_IC: /* [a-z] */
6461  result = ri_lower(curc) || (rex.reg_ic && ri_upper(curc));
6462  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6463  break;
6464 
6465  case NFA_NLOWER_IC: /* [^a-z] */
6466  result = curc != NUL
6467  && !(ri_lower(curc) || (rex.reg_ic && ri_upper(curc)));
6468  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6469  break;
6470 
6471  case NFA_UPPER_IC: /* [A-Z] */
6472  result = ri_upper(curc) || (rex.reg_ic && ri_lower(curc));
6473  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6474  break;
6475 
6476  case NFA_NUPPER_IC: /* ^[A-Z] */
6477  result = curc != NUL
6478  && !(ri_upper(curc) || (rex.reg_ic && ri_lower(curc)));
6479  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6480  break;
6481 
6482  case NFA_BACKREF1:
6483  case NFA_BACKREF2:
6484  case NFA_BACKREF3:
6485  case NFA_BACKREF4:
6486  case NFA_BACKREF5:
6487  case NFA_BACKREF6:
6488  case NFA_BACKREF7:
6489  case NFA_BACKREF8:
6490  case NFA_BACKREF9:
6491 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
6492  case NFA_ZREF1:
6493  case NFA_ZREF2:
6494  case NFA_ZREF3:
6495  case NFA_ZREF4:
6496  case NFA_ZREF5:
6497  case NFA_ZREF6:
6498  case NFA_ZREF7:
6499  case NFA_ZREF8:
6500  case NFA_ZREF9:
6501 #endif
6502  /* \1 .. \9 \z1 .. \z9 */
6503  {
6504  int subidx;
6505  int bytelen;
6506 
6507  if (t->state->c <= NFA_BACKREF9)
6508  {
6509  subidx = t->state->c - NFA_BACKREF1 + 1;
6510  result = match_backref(&t->subs.norm, subidx, &bytelen);
6511  }
6512 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
6513  else
6514  {
6515  subidx = t->state->c - NFA_ZREF1 + 1;
6516  result = match_zref(subidx, &bytelen);
6517  }
6518 #endif
6519 
6520  if (result)
6521  {
6522  if (bytelen == 0)
6523  {
6524  /* empty match always works, output of NFA_SKIP to be
6525  * used next */
6526  add_here = TRUE;
6527  add_state = t->state->out->out;
6528  }
6529  else if (bytelen <= clen)
6530  {
6531  /* match current character, jump ahead to out of
6532  * NFA_SKIP */
6533  add_state = t->state->out->out;
6534  add_off = clen;
6535  }
6536  else
6537  {
6538  /* skip over the matched characters, set character
6539  * count in NFA_SKIP */
6540  add_state = t->state->out;
6541  add_off = bytelen;
6542  add_count = bytelen - clen;
6543  }
6544  }
6545  break;
6546  }
6547  case NFA_SKIP:
6548  /* character of previous matching \1 .. \9 or \@> */
6549  if (t->count - clen <= 0)
6550  {
6551  /* end of match, go to what follows */
6552  add_state = t->state->out;
6553  add_off = clen;
6554  }
6555  else
6556  {
6557  /* add state again with decremented count */
6558  add_state = t->state;
6559  add_off = 0;
6560  add_count = t->count - clen;
6561  }
6562  break;
6563 
6564  case NFA_LNUM:
6565  case NFA_LNUM_GT:
6566  case NFA_LNUM_LT:
6567  result = (REG_MULTI &&
6568  nfa_re_num_cmp(t->state->val, t->state->c - NFA_LNUM,
6569  (long_u)(rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum)));
6570  if (result)
6571  {
6572  add_here = TRUE;
6573  add_state = t->state->out;
6574  }
6575  break;
6576 
6577  case NFA_COL:
6578  case NFA_COL_GT:
6579  case NFA_COL_LT:
6580  result = nfa_re_num_cmp(t->state->val, t->state->c - NFA_COL,
6581  (long_u)(rex.input - rex.line) + 1);
6582  if (result)
6583  {
6584  add_here = TRUE;
6585  add_state = t->state->out;
6586  }
6587  break;
6588 
6589  case NFA_VCOL:
6590  case NFA_VCOL_GT:
6591  case NFA_VCOL_LT:
6592  {
6593  int op = t->state->c - NFA_VCOL;
6594  colnr_T col = (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line);
6595  win_T *wp = rex.reg_win == NULL ? curwin : rex.reg_win;
6596 
6597  /* Bail out quickly when there can't be a match, avoid the
6598  * overhead of win_linetabsize() on long lines. */
6599  if (op != 1 && col > t->state->val
6600  * (has_mbyte ? MB_MAXBYTES : 1))
6601  break;
6602  result = FALSE;
6603  if (op == 1 && col - 1 > t->state->val && col > 100)
6604  {
6605  int ts = wp->w_buffer->b_p_ts;
6606 
6607  /* Guess that a character won't use more columns than
6608  * 'tabstop', with a minimum of 4. */
6609  if (ts < 4)
6610  ts = 4;
6611  result = col > t->state->val * ts;
6612  }
6613  if (!result)
6614  result = nfa_re_num_cmp(t->state->val, op,
6615  (long_u)win_linetabsize(wp, rex.line, col) + 1);
6616  if (result)
6617  {
6618  add_here = TRUE;
6619  add_state = t->state->out;
6620  }
6621  }
6622  break;
6623 
6624  case NFA_MARK:
6625  case NFA_MARK_GT:
6626  case NFA_MARK_LT:
6627  {
6628  pos_T *pos = getmark_buf(rex.reg_buf, t->state->val, FALSE);
6629 
6630  /* Compare the mark position to the match position. */
6631  result = (pos != NULL /* mark doesn't exist */
6632  && pos->lnum > 0 /* mark isn't set in reg_buf */
6633  && (pos->lnum == rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum
6634  ? (pos->col == (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line)
6635  ? t->state->c == NFA_MARK
6636  : (pos->col < (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line)
6637  ? t->state->c == NFA_MARK_GT
6638  : t->state->c == NFA_MARK_LT))
6639  : (pos->lnum < rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum
6640  ? t->state->c == NFA_MARK_GT
6641  : t->state->c == NFA_MARK_LT)));
6642  if (result)
6643  {
6644  add_here = TRUE;
6645  add_state = t->state->out;
6646  }
6647  break;
6648  }
6649 
6650  case NFA_CURSOR:
6651  result = (rex.reg_win != NULL
6652  && (rex.lnum + rex.reg_firstlnum
6653  == rex.reg_win->w_cursor.lnum)
6654  && ((colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line)
6655  == rex.reg_win->w_cursor.col));
6656  if (result)
6657  {
6658  add_here = TRUE;
6659  add_state = t->state->out;
6660  }
6661  break;
6662 
6663  case NFA_VISUAL:
6664  result = reg_match_visual();
6665  if (result)
6666  {
6667  add_here = TRUE;
6668  add_state = t->state->out;
6669  }
6670  break;
6671 
6672  case NFA_MOPEN1:
6673  case NFA_MOPEN2:
6674  case NFA_MOPEN3:
6675  case NFA_MOPEN4:
6676  case NFA_MOPEN5:
6677  case NFA_MOPEN6:
6678  case NFA_MOPEN7:
6679  case NFA_MOPEN8:
6680  case NFA_MOPEN9:
6681 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
6682  case NFA_ZOPEN:
6683  case NFA_ZOPEN1:
6684  case NFA_ZOPEN2:
6685  case NFA_ZOPEN3:
6686  case NFA_ZOPEN4:
6687  case NFA_ZOPEN5:
6688  case NFA_ZOPEN6:
6689  case NFA_ZOPEN7:
6690  case NFA_ZOPEN8:
6691  case NFA_ZOPEN9:
6692 #endif
6693  case NFA_NOPEN:
6694  case NFA_ZSTART:
6695  /* These states are only added to be able to bail out when
6696  * they are added again, nothing is to be done. */
6697  break;
6698 
6699  default: /* regular character */
6700  {
6701  int c = t->state->c;
6702 
6703 #ifdef DEBUG
6704  if (c < 0)
6705  siemsg("INTERNAL: Negative state char: %ld", c);
6706 #endif
6707  result = (c == curc);
6708 
6709  if (!result && rex.reg_ic)
6710  result = MB_TOLOWER(c) == MB_TOLOWER(curc);
6711  /* If rex.reg_icombine is not set only skip over the character
6712  * itself. When it is set skip over composing characters. */
6713  if (result && enc_utf8 && !rex.reg_icombine)
6714  clen = utf_ptr2len(rex.input);
6715  ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH(t->state);
6716  break;
6717  }
6718 
6719  } /* switch (t->state->c) */
6720 
6721  if (add_state != NULL)
6722  {
6723  nfa_pim_T *pim;
6724  nfa_pim_T pim_copy;
6725 
6726  if (t->pim.result == NFA_PIM_UNUSED)
6727  pim = NULL;
6728  else
6729  pim = &t->pim;
6730 
6731  /* Handle the postponed invisible match if the match might end
6732  * without advancing and before the end of the line. */
6733  if (pim != NULL && (clen == 0 || match_follows(add_state, 0)))
6734  {
6735  if (pim->result == NFA_PIM_TODO)
6736  {
6737 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
6738  fprintf(log_fd, "\n");
6739  fprintf(log_fd, "==================================\n");
6740  fprintf(log_fd, "Postponed recursive nfa_regmatch()\n");
6741  fprintf(log_fd, "\n");
6742 #endif
6743  result = recursive_regmatch(pim->state, pim,
6744  prog, submatch, m, &listids, &listids_len);
6745  pim->result = result ? NFA_PIM_MATCH : NFA_PIM_NOMATCH;
6746  /* for \@! and \@<! it is a match when the result is
6747  * FALSE */
6748  if (result != (pim->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG
6749  || pim->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG_FIRST
6750  || pim->state->c
6751  == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG
6752  || pim->state->c
6753  == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST))
6754  {
6755  /* Copy submatch info from the recursive call */
6756  copy_sub_off(&pim->subs.norm, &m->norm);
6757 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
6758  if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr)
6759  copy_sub_off(&pim->subs.synt, &m->synt);
6760 #endif
6761  }
6762  }
6763  else
6764  {
6765  result = (pim->result == NFA_PIM_MATCH);
6766 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
6767  fprintf(log_fd, "\n");
6768  fprintf(log_fd, "Using previous recursive nfa_regmatch() result, result == %d\n", pim->result);
6769  fprintf(log_fd, "MATCH = %s\n", result == TRUE ? "OK" : "FALSE");
6770  fprintf(log_fd, "\n");
6771 #endif
6772  }
6773 
6774  /* for \@! and \@<! it is a match when result is FALSE */
6775  if (result != (pim->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG
6776  || pim->state->c == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_NEG_FIRST
6777  || pim->state->c
6778  == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG
6779  || pim->state->c
6780  == NFA_START_INVISIBLE_BEFORE_NEG_FIRST))
6781  {
6782  /* Copy submatch info from the recursive call */
6783  copy_sub_off(&t->subs.norm, &pim->subs.norm);
6784 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
6785  if (rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr)
6786  copy_sub_off(&t->subs.synt, &pim->subs.synt);
6787 #endif
6788  }
6789  else
6790  /* look-behind match failed, don't add the state */
6791  continue;
6792 
6793  /* Postponed invisible match was handled, don't add it to
6794  * following states. */
6795  pim = NULL;
6796  }
6797 
6798  /* If "pim" points into l->t it will become invalid when
6799  * adding the state causes the list to be reallocated. Make a
6800  * local copy to avoid that. */
6801  if (pim == &t->pim)
6802  {
6803  copy_pim(&pim_copy, pim);
6804  pim = &pim_copy;
6805  }
6806 
6807  if (add_here)
6808  r = addstate_here(thislist, add_state, &t->subs,
6809  pim, &listidx);
6810  else
6811  {
6812  r = addstate(nextlist, add_state, &t->subs, pim, add_off);
6813  if (add_count > 0)
6814  nextlist->t[nextlist->n - 1].count = add_count;
6815  }
6816  if (r == NULL)
6817  {
6818  nfa_match = NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE;
6819  goto theend;
6820  }
6821  }
6822 
6823  } /* for (thislist = thislist; thislist->state; thislist++) */
6824 
6825  /* Look for the start of a match in the current position by adding the
6826  * start state to the list of states.
6827  * The first found match is the leftmost one, thus the order of states
6828  * matters!
6829  * Do not add the start state in recursive calls of nfa_regmatch(),
6830  * because recursive calls should only start in the first position.
6831  * Unless "nfa_endp" is not NULL, then we match the end position.
6832  * Also don't start a match past the first line. */
6833  if (nfa_match == FALSE
6834  && ((toplevel
6835  && rex.lnum == 0
6836  && clen != 0
6837  && (rex.reg_maxcol == 0
6838  || (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line) < rex.reg_maxcol))
6839  || (nfa_endp != NULL
6840  && (REG_MULTI
6841  ? (rex.lnum < nfa_endp->se_u.pos.lnum
6842  || (rex.lnum == nfa_endp->se_u.pos.lnum
6843  && (int)(rex.input - rex.line)
6844  < nfa_endp->se_u.pos.col))
6845  : rex.input < nfa_endp->se_u.ptr))))
6846  {
6847 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
6848  fprintf(log_fd, "(---) STARTSTATE\n");
6849 #endif
6850  /* Inline optimized code for addstate() if we know the state is
6851  * the first MOPEN. */
6852  if (toplevel)
6853  {
6854  int add = TRUE;
6855  int c;
6856 
6857  if (prog->regstart != NUL && clen != 0)
6858  {
6859  if (nextlist->n == 0)
6860  {
6861  colnr_T col = (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line) + clen;
6862 
6863  /* Nextlist is empty, we can skip ahead to the
6864  * character that must appear at the start. */
6865  if (skip_to_start(prog->regstart, &col) == FAIL)
6866  break;
6867 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
6868  fprintf(log_fd, " Skipping ahead %d bytes to regstart\n",
6869  col - ((colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line) + clen));
6870 #endif
6871  rex.input = rex.line + col - clen;
6872  }
6873  else
6874  {
6875  /* Checking if the required start character matches is
6876  * cheaper than adding a state that won't match. */
6877  c = PTR2CHAR(rex.input + clen);
6878  if (c != prog->regstart && (!rex.reg_ic
6879  || MB_TOLOWER(c) != MB_TOLOWER(prog->regstart)))
6880  {
6881 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
6882  fprintf(log_fd, " Skipping start state, regstart does not match\n");
6883 #endif
6884  add = FALSE;
6885  }
6886  }
6887  }
6888 
6889  if (add)
6890  {
6891  if (REG_MULTI)
6892  m->norm.list.multi[0].start_col =
6893  (colnr_T)(rex.input - rex.line) + clen;
6894  else
6895  m->norm.list.line[0].start = rex.input + clen;
6896  if (addstate(nextlist, start->out, m, NULL, clen) == NULL)
6897  {
6898  nfa_match = NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE;
6899  goto theend;
6900  }
6901  }
6902  }
6903  else
6904  {
6905  if (addstate(nextlist, start, m, NULL, clen) == NULL)
6906  {
6907  nfa_match = NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE;
6908  goto theend;
6909  }
6910  }
6911  }
6912 
6913 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
6914  fprintf(log_fd, ">>> Thislist had %d states available: ", thislist->n);
6915  {
6916  int i;
6917 
6918  for (i = 0; i < thislist->n; i++)
6919  fprintf(log_fd, "%d ", abs(thislist->t[i].state->id));
6920  }
6921  fprintf(log_fd, "\n");
6922 #endif
6923 
6924 nextchar:
6925  /* Advance to the next character, or advance to the next line, or
6926  * finish. */
6927  if (clen != 0)
6928  rex.input += clen;
6929  else if (go_to_nextline || (nfa_endp != NULL && REG_MULTI
6930  && rex.lnum < nfa_endp->se_u.pos.lnum))
6931  reg_nextline();
6932  else
6933  break;
6934 
6935  /* Allow interrupting with CTRL-C. */
6936  line_breakcheck();
6937  if (got_int)
6938  break;
6939 #ifdef FEAT_RELTIME
6940  /* Check for timeout once in a twenty times to avoid overhead. */
6941  if (nfa_time_limit != NULL && ++nfa_time_count == 20)
6942  {
6943  nfa_time_count = 0;
6944  if (nfa_did_time_out())
6945  break;
6946  }
6947 #endif
6948  }
6949 
6950 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
6951  if (log_fd != stderr)
6952  fclose(log_fd);
6953  log_fd = NULL;
6954 #endif
6955 
6956 theend:
6957  /* Free memory */
6958  vim_free(list[0].t);
6959  vim_free(list[1].t);
6960  vim_free(listids);
6961 #undef ADD_STATE_IF_MATCH
6962 #ifdef NFA_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG
6963  fclose(debug);
6964 #endif
6965 
6966  return nfa_match;
6967 }
6968 
6969 /*
6970  * Try match of "prog" with at rex.line["col"].
6971  * Returns <= 0 for failure, number of lines contained in the match otherwise.
6972  */
6973  static long
6974 nfa_regtry(
6975  nfa_regprog_T *prog,
6976  colnr_T col,
6977  proftime_T *tm UNUSED, /* timeout limit or NULL */
6978  int *timed_out UNUSED) /* flag set on timeout or NULL */
6979 {
6980  int i;
6981  regsubs_T subs, m;
6982  nfa_state_T *start = prog->start;
6983  int result;
6984 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
6985  FILE *f;
6986 #endif
6987 
6988  rex.input = rex.line + col;
6989 #ifdef FEAT_RELTIME
6990  nfa_time_limit = tm;
6991  nfa_timed_out = timed_out;
6992  nfa_time_count = 0;
6993 #endif
6994 
6995 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
6996  f = fopen(NFA_REGEXP_RUN_LOG, "a");
6997  if (f != NULL)
6998  {
6999  fprintf(f, "\n\n\t=======================================================\n");
7000 #ifdef DEBUG
7001  fprintf(f, "\tRegexp is \"%s\"\n", nfa_regengine.expr);
7002 #endif
7003  fprintf(f, "\tInput text is \"%s\" \n", rex.input);
7004  fprintf(f, "\t=======================================================\n\n");
7005  nfa_print_state(f, start);
7006  fprintf(f, "\n\n");
7007  fclose(f);
7008  }
7009  else
7010  emsg("Could not open temporary log file for writing");
7011 #endif
7012 
7013  clear_sub(&subs.norm);
7014  clear_sub(&m.norm);
7015 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
7016  clear_sub(&subs.synt);
7017  clear_sub(&m.synt);
7018 #endif
7019 
7020  result = nfa_regmatch(prog, start, &subs, &m);
7021  if (result == FALSE)
7022  return 0;
7023  else if (result == NFA_TOO_EXPENSIVE)
7024  return result;
7025 
7026  cleanup_subexpr();
7027  if (REG_MULTI)
7028  {
7029  for (i = 0; i < subs.norm.in_use; i++)
7030  {
7031  rex.reg_startpos[i].lnum = subs.norm.list.multi[i].start_lnum;
7032  rex.reg_startpos[i].col = subs.norm.list.multi[i].start_col;
7033 
7034  rex.reg_endpos[i].lnum = subs.norm.list.multi[i].end_lnum;
7035  rex.reg_endpos[i].col = subs.norm.list.multi[i].end_col;
7036  }
7037 
7038  if (rex.reg_startpos[0].lnum < 0)
7039  {
7040  rex.reg_startpos[0].lnum = 0;
7041  rex.reg_startpos[0].col = col;
7042  }
7043  if (rex.reg_endpos[0].lnum < 0)
7044  {
7045  /* pattern has a \ze but it didn't match, use current end */
7046  rex.reg_endpos[0].lnum = rex.lnum;
7047  rex.reg_endpos[0].col = (int)(rex.input - rex.line);
7048  }
7049  else
7050  /* Use line number of "\ze". */
7051  rex.lnum = rex.reg_endpos[0].lnum;
7052  }
7053  else
7054  {
7055  for (i = 0; i < subs.norm.in_use; i++)
7056  {
7057  rex.reg_startp[i] = subs.norm.list.line[i].start;
7058  rex.reg_endp[i] = subs.norm.list.line[i].end;
7059  }
7060 
7061  if (rex.reg_startp[0] == NULL)
7062  rex.reg_startp[0] = rex.line + col;
7063  if (rex.reg_endp[0] == NULL)
7064  rex.reg_endp[0] = rex.input;
7065  }
7066 
7067 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
7068  /* Package any found \z(...\) matches for export. Default is none. */
7069  unref_extmatch(re_extmatch_out);
7070  re_extmatch_out = NULL;
7071 
7072  if (prog->reghasz == REX_SET)
7073  {
7074  cleanup_zsubexpr();
7075  re_extmatch_out = make_extmatch();
7076  /* Loop over \z1, \z2, etc. There is no \z0. */
7077  for (i = 1; i < subs.synt.in_use; i++)
7078  {
7079  if (REG_MULTI)
7080  {
7081  struct multipos *mpos = &subs.synt.list.multi[i];
7082 
7083  /* Only accept single line matches that are valid. */
7084  if (mpos->start_lnum >= 0
7085  && mpos->start_lnum == mpos->end_lnum
7086  && mpos->end_col >= mpos->start_col)
7087  re_extmatch_out->matches[i] =
7088  vim_strnsave(reg_getline(mpos->start_lnum)
7089  + mpos->start_col,
7090  mpos->end_col - mpos->start_col);
7091  }
7092  else
7093  {
7094  struct linepos *lpos = &subs.synt.list.line[i];
7095 
7096  if (lpos->start != NULL && lpos->end != NULL)
7097  re_extmatch_out->matches[i] =
7098  vim_strnsave(lpos->start,
7099  (int)(lpos->end - lpos->start));
7100  }
7101  }
7102  }
7103 #endif
7104 
7105  return 1 + rex.lnum;
7106 }
7107 
7108 /*
7109  * Match a regexp against a string ("line" points to the string) or multiple
7110  * lines ("line" is NULL, use reg_getline()).
7111  *
7112  * Returns <= 0 for failure, number of lines contained in the match otherwise.
7113  */
7114  static long
7115 nfa_regexec_both(
7116  char_u *line,
7117  colnr_T startcol, /* column to start looking for match */
7118  proftime_T *tm, /* timeout limit or NULL */
7119  int *timed_out) /* flag set on timeout or NULL */
7120 {
7121  nfa_regprog_T *prog;
7122  long retval = 0L;
7123  int i;
7124  colnr_T col = startcol;
7125 
7126  if (REG_MULTI)
7127  {
7128  prog = (nfa_regprog_T *)rex.reg_mmatch->regprog;
7129  line = reg_getline((linenr_T)0); /* relative to the cursor */
7130  rex.reg_startpos = rex.reg_mmatch->startpos;
7131  rex.reg_endpos = rex.reg_mmatch->endpos;
7132  }
7133  else
7134  {
7135  prog = (nfa_regprog_T *)rex.reg_match->regprog;
7136  rex.reg_startp = rex.reg_match->startp;
7137  rex.reg_endp = rex.reg_match->endp;
7138  }
7139 
7140  /* Be paranoid... */
7141  if (prog == NULL || line == NULL)
7142  {
7143  emsg(_(e_null));
7144  goto theend;
7145  }
7146 
7147  /* If pattern contains "\c" or "\C": overrule value of rex.reg_ic */
7148  if (prog->regflags & RF_ICASE)
7149  rex.reg_ic = TRUE;
7150  else if (prog->regflags & RF_NOICASE)
7151  rex.reg_ic = FALSE;
7152 
7153  /* If pattern contains "\Z" overrule value of rex.reg_icombine */
7154  if (prog->regflags & RF_ICOMBINE)
7155  rex.reg_icombine = TRUE;
7156 
7157  rex.line = line;
7158  rex.lnum = 0; /* relative to line */
7159 
7160  rex.nfa_has_zend = prog->has_zend;
