7161  rex.nfa_has_backref = prog->has_backref;
7162  rex.nfa_nsubexpr = prog->nsubexp;
7163  rex.nfa_listid = 1;
7164  rex.nfa_alt_listid = 2;
7165 #ifdef DEBUG
7166  nfa_regengine.expr = prog->pattern;
7167 #endif
7168 
7169  if (prog->reganch && col > 0)
7170  return 0L;
7171 
7172  rex.need_clear_subexpr = TRUE;
7173 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
7174  /* Clear the external match subpointers if necessary. */
7175  if (prog->reghasz == REX_SET)
7176  {
7177  rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr = TRUE;
7178  rex.need_clear_zsubexpr = TRUE;
7179  }
7180  else
7181  {
7182  rex.nfa_has_zsubexpr = FALSE;
7183  rex.need_clear_zsubexpr = FALSE;
7184  }
7185 #endif
7186 
7187  if (prog->regstart != NUL)
7188  {
7189  /* Skip ahead until a character we know the match must start with.
7190  * When there is none there is no match. */
7191  if (skip_to_start(prog->regstart, &col) == FAIL)
7192  return 0L;
7193 
7194  /* If match_text is set it contains the full text that must match.
7195  * Nothing else to try. Doesn't handle combining chars well. */
7196  if (prog->match_text != NULL && !rex.reg_icombine)
7197  return find_match_text(col, prog->regstart, prog->match_text);
7198  }
7199 
7200  /* If the start column is past the maximum column: no need to try. */
7201  if (rex.reg_maxcol > 0 && col >= rex.reg_maxcol)
7202  goto theend;
7203 
7204  // Set the "nstate" used by nfa_regcomp() to zero to trigger an error when
7205  // it's accidentally used during execution.
7206  nstate = 0;
7207  for (i = 0; i < prog->nstate; ++i)
7208  {
7209  prog->state[i].id = i;
7210  prog->state[i].lastlist[0] = 0;
7211  prog->state[i].lastlist[1] = 0;
7212  }
7213 
7214  retval = nfa_regtry(prog, col, tm, timed_out);
7215 
7216 #ifdef DEBUG
7217  nfa_regengine.expr = NULL;
7218 #endif
7219 
7220 theend:
7221  return retval;
7222 }
7223 
7224 /*
7225  * Compile a regular expression into internal code for the NFA matcher.
7226  * Returns the program in allocated space. Returns NULL for an error.
7227  */
7228  static regprog_T *
7229 nfa_regcomp(char_u *expr, int re_flags)
7230 {
7231  nfa_regprog_T *prog = NULL;
7232  size_t prog_size;
7233  int *postfix;
7234 
7235  if (expr == NULL)
7236  return NULL;
7237 
7238 #ifdef DEBUG
7239  nfa_regengine.expr = expr;
7240 #endif
7241  nfa_re_flags = re_flags;
7242 
7243  init_class_tab();
7244 
7245  if (nfa_regcomp_start(expr, re_flags) == FAIL)
7246  return NULL;
7247 
7248  /* Build postfix form of the regexp. Needed to build the NFA
7249  * (and count its size). */
7250  postfix = re2post();
7251  if (postfix == NULL)
7252  goto fail; /* Cascaded (syntax?) error */
7253 
7254  /*
7255  * In order to build the NFA, we parse the input regexp twice:
7256  * 1. first pass to count size (so we can allocate space)
7257  * 2. second to emit code
7258  */
7259 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
7260  {
7261  FILE *f = fopen(NFA_REGEXP_RUN_LOG, "a");
7262 
7263  if (f != NULL)
7264  {
7265  fprintf(f, "\n*****************************\n\n\n\n\tCompiling regexp \"%s\"... hold on !\n", expr);
7266  fclose(f);
7267  }
7268  }
7269 #endif
7270 
7271  /*
7272  * PASS 1
7273  * Count number of NFA states in "nstate". Do not build the NFA.
7274  */
7275  post2nfa(postfix, post_ptr, TRUE);
7276 
7277  /* allocate the regprog with space for the compiled regexp */
7278  prog_size = sizeof(nfa_regprog_T) + sizeof(nfa_state_T) * (nstate - 1);
7279  prog = alloc(prog_size);
7280  if (prog == NULL)
7281  goto fail;
7282  state_ptr = prog->state;
7283  prog->re_in_use = FALSE;
7284 
7285  /*
7286  * PASS 2
7287  * Build the NFA
7288  */
7289  prog->start = post2nfa(postfix, post_ptr, FALSE);
7290  if (prog->start == NULL)
7291  goto fail;
7292 
7293  prog->regflags = regflags;
7294  prog->engine = &nfa_regengine;
7295  prog->nstate = nstate;
7296  prog->has_zend = rex.nfa_has_zend;
7297  prog->has_backref = rex.nfa_has_backref;
7298  prog->nsubexp = regnpar;
7299 
7300  nfa_postprocess(prog);
7301 
7302  prog->reganch = nfa_get_reganch(prog->start, 0);
7303  prog->regstart = nfa_get_regstart(prog->start, 0);
7304  prog->match_text = nfa_get_match_text(prog->start);
7305 
7306 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
7307  nfa_postfix_dump(expr, OK);
7308  nfa_dump(prog);
7309 #endif
7310 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
7311  /* Remember whether this pattern has any \z specials in it. */
7312  prog->reghasz = re_has_z;
7313 #endif
7314  prog->pattern = vim_strsave(expr);
7315 #ifdef DEBUG
7316  nfa_regengine.expr = NULL;
7317 #endif
7318 
7319 out:
7320  VIM_CLEAR(post_start);
7321  post_ptr = post_end = NULL;
7322  state_ptr = NULL;
7323  return (regprog_T *)prog;
7324 
7325 fail:
7326  VIM_CLEAR(prog);
7327 #ifdef ENABLE_LOG
7328  nfa_postfix_dump(expr, FAIL);
7329 #endif
7330 #ifdef DEBUG
7331  nfa_regengine.expr = NULL;
7332 #endif
7333  goto out;
7334 }
7335 
7336 /*
7337  * Free a compiled regexp program, returned by nfa_regcomp().
7338  */
7339  static void
7340 nfa_regfree(regprog_T *prog)
7341 {
7342  if (prog != NULL)
7343  {
7344  vim_free(((nfa_regprog_T *)prog)->match_text);
7345  vim_free(((nfa_regprog_T *)prog)->pattern);
7346  vim_free(prog);
7347  }
7348 }

7350 /*
7351  * Match a regexp against a string.
7352  * "rmp->regprog" is a compiled regexp as returned by nfa_regcomp().
7353  * Uses curbuf for line count and 'iskeyword'.
7354  * If "line_lbr" is TRUE consider a "\n" in "line" to be a line break.
7355  *
7356  * Returns <= 0 for failure, number of lines contained in the match otherwise.
7357  */
7358  static int
7359 nfa_regexec_nl(
7360  regmatch_T *rmp,
7361  char_u *line, /* string to match against */
7362  colnr_T col, /* column to start looking for match */
7363  int line_lbr)
7364 {
7365  rex.reg_match = rmp;
7366  rex.reg_mmatch = NULL;
7367  rex.reg_maxline = 0;
7368  rex.reg_line_lbr = line_lbr;
7369  rex.reg_buf = curbuf;
7370  rex.reg_win = NULL;
7371  rex.reg_ic = rmp->rm_ic;
7372  rex.reg_icombine = FALSE;
7373  rex.reg_maxcol = 0;
7374  return nfa_regexec_both(line, col, NULL, NULL);

7378 /*
7379  * Match a regexp against multiple lines.
7380  * "rmp->regprog" is a compiled regexp as returned by vim_regcomp().
7381  * Uses curbuf for line count and 'iskeyword'.
7382  *
7383  * Return <= 0 if there is no match. Return number of lines contained in the
7384  * match otherwise.
7385  *
7386  * Note: the body is the same as bt_regexec() except for nfa_regexec_both()
7387  *
7388  * ! Also NOTE : match may actually be in another line. e.g.:
7389  * when r.e. is \nc, cursor is at 'a' and the text buffer looks like
7390  *
7391  * +-------------------------+
7392  * |a |
7393  * |b |
7394  * |c |
7395  * | |
7396  * +-------------------------+
7397  *
7398  * then nfa_regexec_multi() returns 3. while the original
7399  * vim_regexec_multi() returns 0 and a second call at line 2 will return 2.
7400  *
7401  * FIXME if this behavior is not compatible.
7402  */
7403  static long
7404 nfa_regexec_multi(
7405  regmmatch_T *rmp,
7406  win_T *win, /* window in which to search or NULL */
7407  buf_T *buf, /* buffer in which to search */
7408  linenr_T lnum, /* nr of line to start looking for match */
7409  colnr_T col, /* column to start looking for match */
7410  proftime_T *tm, /* timeout limit or NULL */
7411  int *timed_out) /* flag set on timeout or NULL */
7412 {
7413  rex.reg_match = NULL;
7414  rex.reg_mmatch = rmp;
7415  rex.reg_buf = buf;
7416  rex.reg_win = win;
7417  rex.reg_firstlnum = lnum;
7418  rex.reg_maxline = rex.reg_buf->b_ml.ml_line_count - lnum;
7419  rex.reg_line_lbr = FALSE;
7420  rex.reg_ic = rmp->rmm_ic;
7421  rex.reg_icombine = FALSE;
7422  rex.reg_maxcol = rmp->rmm_maxcol;
7423 
7424  return nfa_regexec_both(NULL, col, tm, timed_out);
7425 }
